name: PHYTO-PIGMENTS Flawless Serum Foundation
reviews-text:
I am a huge fan of clean and organic beauty. I have been trying to transition for a bit and this is my new favorite foundation. For me, if I pair this with the CC cream underneath, it helps keep my skin moisturized. At first, the foundation seems hard to blend with a sponge. However, I talked to a JB vendor and she said the best way to get the most out of a pump is by placing on back of hand and moving in circular motions. Then with clean hands place a little of the foundation on face and blend with a sponge. That process has been working wonderfully and it gives great coverage. So happy I found this foundation. Also, if you have drier skin, or just want to add more to it, you can put one or two drops of a serum like hyaluronic acid or vitamin C. This helps to blend the foundation too. Girls, take the steps to go more organic and natural with your makeup and skincare. 
You won't regret it.

reviews-text: I used liquid foundation most of my life but I absolutely hate the feeling. I feel like my skin can't breathe so in the past couple years I started using powder foundation. I have very neutral undertones to my skin and most foundation looks pink on me. This doesn't. It matches extremely well. I was using BareMinerals powder foundation before this and it made my face look really white even though it was my supposed shade. I love the natural glow to it and how my skin can breathe with it on. I only have a couple minor complaints. It comes off the end of my nose after a couple hours but it could be from rubbing my nose due to allergies. With it being luminous, it accentuates my larger pores on my cheeks. I have bought the Celebration Foundation in the matte form and use it on my nose and cheeks and use this everywhere else. Problem has been solved. It's twice as expensive but they last twice as long. I will and have repurchased. Definitely recommend if you like powder foundation.

I bought this product to cover a part of my tattoo for work. It will cover it when you are dabbing it on. But I don't want my chest to look cakey.  As soon as you go to blend it out it doesn't cover the tattoo at all. No matter how I tried blending it, it just wouldn't cover it.

One plus though is I tried using it on my face and it covered my blackheads pretty good.

When I layered it, I got medium coverage. I don't over saturate my sponge either. This can cling to dry patches and look c...

name: Studio Fix Powder Plus Foundation
reviews-text: I was surprised at the coverage it gave me with such little powder I used! I used the virtual live try on of the foundation, and looked at the reviews before buying... I'm very happy, and pleased with the wear of it today!! Glad I took the plunge and bought it

product-links: Studio Fix Soft Matte Foundation Stick
name: Studio Fix Soft Matte Foundation Stick
reviews-text: Even with a damp makeup sponge/beauty blender, this product is tough to blend. I use this color in other MAC foundations and this one seems to be a more orange color. It's a strange foundation; not very natural-looking. I'll stick to the liquid foundations going forward.

name: PRO Soft Focus Longwear Foundation
reviews-text: I love the coverage and how natural it looks in photos

name: Studio Waterweight SPF 30 Foundation
reviews-text: I've been trying to find a natural looking light coverage foundation for ages and nothing has been fitting the bill. The saleswoman at Ulta suggested this product for me and I am completely obsessed! It's very light and natural looking, all my freckles still show through, but it evens out my skin tone and just softens the look. I've been using my Born This Way concealer afterward for spots where I want a little more coverage and they blend together perfectly. I do find that my skin starts to get a little oily/shiny later in the day (I have relatively dry skin), but adding translucent powder on top of the foundation has been helping, and the pros of the foundation outweigh this slight annoyance for me.

name: InstaBake Aqua Glass Foundation
reviews-text: Amazing! Makes you looked airbrushes and flawless. Keeps oil at bay and this is coming from a very oily skinned girl!

product-links: No Makeup Foundation Broad Spectrum SPF 20
name: No Makeup Foundation Broad Spectrum SPF 20
reviews-text: The name no foundation foundation is perfect as it never looks like makeup but blends with skin tones  it seems to cover without looking like a coverup, Also it feels good like nothing is on my skin.

name: Rénergie Lift Makeup Foundation SPF 27
reviews-text: Just like other reviewers have stated - this new formula SUCKS.I have been using this foundation in 250 bisque (W) for 10 years. It was my holy grail foundation, hands down the best foundation EVER for me. It matched my skin tone PERFECTLY, the coverage was beautiful, the glow was gorgeous, it was just an amazing foundation all round. I needed a new bottle so I came online and at first I was surprised to even read that the formula had changed. I was disappointed but still held some hope that maybe the new formula wasn't as bad as people were saying. Welp... they were right. It's awful. My undertone is warm and this new formula is ORANGE (see picture). It doesn't even seem to have that dewy finish. Everything that was fantastic about this foundation is now gone. Not to mention the price is now higher. This foundation is garbage. I am returning it and finding something comparable, I have heard good things about Diorskin so maybe I'll try that. Lancome WHY OH WHY would you go and ruin the most perfect foundation there ever was? Blows my mind.
review-keyword: Lancome has lost another long-term customer

name: SuperStay Full Coverage Powder Foundation
reviews-text: I've been looking for a powder that I can wear to work so I don't look tired. I have oily skin, and it sits fine on my skin. I feel the coverage is more medium than full, but it's buildable. it is lightweight and has been keeping my oily shine undercontrol. I don't touch it up while at work, so it does last long. it's not bad for the price. I'd recommend it.

name: Absolute Cover Foundation
reviews-text:
I have combination/oily skin and this looked absolutely terrible on me. I tried primer/no primer—powder/no powder—setting spray/no spray. No combination I used seemed to work. I either ended up looking super cakey or the foundation completely disappeared throughout the day. 
It oxidized like crazy and I was orange within an hour. 
The coverage wasn't spectacular but I was able to build it. 
I'm not sure if dryer skin types would have better luck with this but I wouldn't necessarily suggest this for combo skin.

I was so disappointed when I could no longer buy it at my local, I hope you guys can bring it back please.

name: Micro Silque Foundation
reviews-text: I really wanted to love this foundation. It goes on smoothly, but that is where it stops. Within 2 hours it oxides and leaves a an ugly orange tint. It does not hold up for more than 5 hours. There are also limited color options. The neutral is more of a warm.
review-keyword: Love the formula, not the colors

product-links: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation
name: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation
reviews-text:
I really like this as a light coverage foundation but it is finicky. Since it is a loose powder you can't just throw it on top of anything. Use a concealer first that dries down and make sure any primer or moisturizer is totally dry before you use this. I really think no primer is best. and I use a flat dense brush to really buff it in. My favorite is the Sigma F80. If your face is damp anywhere, even just if you are wearing lip balm, this will stick to that moisture and not bled out. You have to buff it in so you will have to buff over your lip line to make it seamless. Just leave your skin void of anything except a concealer that dries down and has already dried. 

Other than that this is luminous and truly blends into my skin to look like skin. The finish is one of the best I own! But if you just slap it on like any powder, or treat it like a regular foundation, you'll hate it.

reviews-text: i strictly only wear foundations that look like skin. i dont care how much coverage it has, as long as its completely unclockable. im a b.b. cream girl at heart, but even those be TOO expensive and the cheap ones are trash. this is the perfect alternative if you want something light, that you can just conceal on top of if needed. i would say this size has lasted me well over a month & i used it daily

reviews-text: I use this foundation every day, and I love it! It is long wearing, looks great all day long, and never dries out my skin.

name: Face Tape Foundation
reviews-text: I have been searching a long time for a full coverage foundation that will last all day, and this one takes the cake! I I am 35 years old with combination skin, and I must say that this is the only foundation that does what it says. it dries down mat, however if you want that glowy look with this foundation I recommend using a hydrating primer. I personally use a matte primer because my forehead gets really oily throughout the day. this foundation does not oxidize on my skin, which I am very prone to for some reason when it comes to most foundations. I'm really surprised that a lot of the negative reviews, perhaps maybe changing the type of primer that you use will help? I really hope that they never stop making this foundation because it is the only one without silica and SPF in it and I am really allergic to SPF. I am on my fourth or fifth bottle now and I don't want to ever by any other foundation.

reviews-text: This is an exact dupe for the Fenty matte foundation. Upon application, it's a soft matte finish that looks really natural. However, I have incredibly oily skin, so after 4-5 hours, I'm shiny, but that is the case with every foundation in the world. It does stay in place, though, when I get oily, and if I add a little powder or blot, I'm back to looking naturally glowy and healthy. If you want a MATTE finish, this isn't it, but if you prefer a natural finish, this is perfect.

name: Tinted Cover Foundation
reviews-text: If you have perfect skin this may work for you. My skin isn't terrible, but the coverage is barely anything, it doesn't lay nicely on the skin, and it turned me into an absolute greaseball. You don't even get a full ounce. Way overpriced for what you get.

At age 72 I need very sheer, lightweight coverage.

It covers all my imperfections and redness perfectly and doesn't feel heavy. Just a warning it does oxidize a little bit so if you are in between shades go with the lighter one. It doesn't bother me as it blends so well that either shade would have worked for me. I will absolutely be purchasing this again in the summer in a darker shade!

I have to use a setting spray (also Cover FX) to get it to last all day, otherwise I get oily after 4 hours, and need to blot my face. I love this foundation so much, that I bought one for my teenage daughter to use. I highly recommend this foundation. It's not cakey or filled with ingredients that will cause skin problems.

reviews-text: The moment I walked into an Ulta store and asked a technician what she thought was the best full coverage foundation was the moment my make-up life changed forever. It covers everything beautifully and makes your skin looks absolutly flawless! Use a good moisturizer (I love Olay in the pink bottle) and primer (Becca or Physicians Formula highligher primer) and that is it!  It's on there until you take it off - sometimes not until 18 hours later.  My absolute Holy Grail!

reviews-text: The one thing I love most about this is it actively works on tackling skin tone unevenness WHILST I'm wearing it - making this not just a foundation but a 'Treatment foundation' if ever there was such a thing! It contains brightening ingredients such as Grapefruit extract, which is why when I wash this off, I swear my skin looks brighter than it did before I put it on! I stopped by at the Clinique counter to find the right match (the SA settled on two shades for me to trial: Oat and Honeywheat, neither of which were quite the right shade for me - 'Tea' was). As a light, non-oily, everyday foundation it works really well, coverage was medium but buildable and without using a primer beforehand, only setting powder after, it stayed put from 8AM in the morning until 5.30PM when I got in from work which is pretty good going. One of the downsides is that on oilier areas like my t-zone, especially on hotter days, it didn't last as long as it did on other areas, my pores becoming fairly visible after several hours, but that's an issue I find with many foundations, not just this one. Also the SPF 15 isn't quite as high as I'd like so I end up applying a sunblock separately before this. It's only the inclusion of sillicones that've prevented me from giving it a full 5 lippies, as I wouldn't be able to use everyday due to the breakout they cause me, otherwise a somewhat unique foundation that goes above and beyond just providing coverage. Good color match too! -> My 'Ulta Beauty Top 7 must-have list' (thought it might be useful to share my 7 favorite beauty products of all time, focusing mainly on my purchases at Ulta) < - < 1. Hair Loss Treatment: Divine Herbal Hair Oil < 2. Eye Cream: Clinique All about eyes < 3. Lip Gloss: Clarins Lip Comfort Oil < 4. Makeup Remover: Lancome Bi Facil < 5. Anti-Aging Serum: Divine Herbal Facial Treatment Serum < 6. Eyeliner: Ulta Beauty Gel Eyeliner Pencil < 7. Moisturizer: 'Lush' – Enzymion
review-keyword: Unique as far as foundations go...

name: Hello Happy Flawless Brightening Foundation
reviews-text: Walked in to the store thinking I'd just buy my usual powder foundation but the sales associate's foundation was glowing and dewy and is-it-great-skin-or-foundation tone...and she was super fair skinned like me! She showed me this product and also a pore minimizer/primer. Bought those two products along with a brush for this foundation. VERY happy with the results and have received many compliments.

name: Dream Radiant Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: Bought this without reading the reviews. I was upset after seeing the reviews about how horrible this foundation. But I still wanted to give it a wear test before returning it. This foundation is REALLY GOOD! it smooths out my pores and it's not drying or flakes off like most people are saying. I can understand how this would come off during the day without a primer and not setting this with a powder those two products are a must with this foundation. I've been wearing it all day and sweated in this foundation and it hasn't settled in my smile like or look cakey. my skin is combo and this doesn't cling onto my dry patches from acne healing like my NYX can't stop won't stop, that foundation is actually way orange and more drying  than this foundation.

name: Pure Radiant Tinted Moisturizer
reviews-text:
I have tried EVERYTHING with my skin. 
A little TMI, but it's hard to find reviews with my specific skin issues!
First off- I have an explanon in my arm (form of birth control). When I was between 18-22, I seriously had great skin with this in, after getting it replaced.... I've had to COMPLETELY revamp my skin routine. (26 now) It's hard to find a balance with foundation products and moisturizers that keep me from breaking out and this product has been a life-saver. Because of the excess oil my skin produces, everything needs to be water based, oil free and non-comedogenic. Although it's not great to have very oily skin, you CANNOT dry it out or else you go back in the reverse direction. Seriously a hard line that you have to teeter on! This product has made me feel confident in my skin by reducing the look of dark spots and uneven skin-tone and gives you that no make-up look that makes you have that 'beautiful-in-your-own skin' kind of feeling! Side note** I wear the dr. Brant pore reducing mattifying primer or the benefit pore primer underneath and my breakouts have reduced significantly! You can wear a little foundation over this if you want that flawless look but it is honestly great without it. (I'd recommend Estée Lauder non-comedogenic). Absolutely feels lightweight even with the added foundation!

For any of you with any similar skin issues- I definitely have tips and tricks if you don't want to go through the years of trial and error that it took for me! Yes, the costs of everything can get you worried, but this is the best my skin has looked and felt in years!

name: Moisturizing Foundation Stick
reviews-text:
ok, so i only bought this bec of the b2g2 free promo. out of the 4 items i purchased this one takes the cake!
i normally am a person who likes a medium to full coverage however i like to switch it up periodically and try something new or perhaps a lighter formula. i am also used to using bb creams as a foundation alone so sheer doesnt bother me. 
to begin this is a sheer to med coverage. i think of it as a dewy type BUT it applies like cream to powder. it does not exactly dry down completely. it stays sheer but kinda sets in place. if u were to rub your face thruout the day it will transfer. i might add i did not wear a primer, powder or setting spray. i wore it alone with cream blush on top. i have combo skin. i used a toner after a clean face then essence as moisturizer then stick directly and blended with finger tips. after 4 hours it didnt move but nothing touched my face. if u have oily skin this may not be for you. this product did not appear patchy. it glided accross my skin. the color payoff is great i bought lt-med neutral bec that is my true skintone and it matched. again this product may transfer if u touch your face but i was working thruout the day and foundation didnt move exvept for my nose i can see oil coming thru but took a good 5 or more hours to see this. i will continue to use this and may purchase again. i did enjoy this product more than i realized. i also bought cream blush, liquid lipstick, shiny lipstick and the youthful glow concealer all by ulta. i felt that the foundation stick had more coverage than the youthful glow concealer for reference

name: Beyond Matte Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: I'm 39, starting to deal with aging skin and dryness.  I knew that I wanted a matte foundation as to not accentuate old acne scars.  At first I was confused when I tried the foundation, because it didn't seem very matte.  I think the name, beyond matte might be a little misleading.  However, when I looked online at the description, it does state that its semi-matte.  So, I should've looked at that closer.  I figured that I would need to send it back, but to my suprise it covered my imperfections and didn't accentuate them.  So,  I was very pleased with that.  I'm still trying to figure out the best method for applying...I didn't like the beauty blender method, using a brush gave the best coverage but can look cakey if you're not careful with the brush.  The color was pretty spot on.  I purchased the lightest color available.  For reference, I have auburn hair and a fair, neutral skin tone.

name: Narcissist Foundation Stick
reviews-text: I've just finished my first stick of this foundation and found it to be just very nice.  I replaced my previous go-to foundation, which was much pricier, which this one, which is much more affordable.  Medium neutral is a perfect match for my skin.  I do use a tiny bit of moisturizer when applying it--normally,  I put it on my fingers, rub them together with a drop of moisturizer/oil, pat it on, and use a sponge or brush to pat/ spread.  I'm 65, combination skin.  I also really like their customer service.

name: Flawless Lumière Radiance-Perfecting Foundation
reviews-text: After having my daughter 2.5 years ago my skin has changed drastically. I used to be a complete vat of oil. I now have desert dry skin and I've been desperately trying to combat this with a complete change in skincare/makeup. This is probably the 5th attempt at foundation. I loved the coverage level. For me, it's as much as I want. Covers my redness and light blemishes while providing a seemingly nice canvas. Ordering by online shade swatches was beyond wacky though. DEFINITELY do this in-store (once Ulta re-opens😢) I've never had such difficulty trying to find a shade match. I'm your basic light/neutral and on my 5th shade it was finally decent. So day #1. Applied with zero primer. Just wanted to see the product work for itself. Applied beautifully. Within a few hours it settled into lines I never knew existed. I looked like I applied a crackly face mask. Full of separation as well. Horrifying. Next I purchased the Laura mercier hydrating primer. I really wanted this to work. It honestly helped tremendously. Better application, more natural finish and minimal separation. Can't say I'd purchase this again because it still isn't perfect, but totally okay with using it until it empties. Here's why I'm really deducting stars... I have been lucky and have had very few blemishes lately, but noticed after wearing this regularly for a week, I've developed intense blackheads. In places I've never in my life had them. Never experienced this ever with any makeup. This was the only addition to my routine so i really can't blame anything else. Another thing... how is NOBODY talking about the fragrance?!? It hit me immediately, and I tried around 5 different shades so I know I'm not crazy!! It's some really odd spicy scent?!!! What is that about?!! Very strange experience overall, but whatever I'm keeping it for the time being.

name: Skin Perfecting Comfort Matte Foundation
reviews-text: I had high hopes for this foundation. I typically only buy high-end foundations due to my sensitive, acne-prone skin, but I thought Almay would be the safest drugstore foundation to buy as the brand seems relatively clean. The foundation looked fine throughout the day, nothing special, but as soon as I removed it at the end of the day I had tiny bumps all along my cheeks. It's been about a year and the scarring is still clearing up. Not sure what ingredients are in this, but I'm certainly afraid to try anything else! Note: I did patch test, but it only irritated specific parts of my face. Super weird.

product-links: Clear Complexion Make Myself Clear Makeup
name: Clear Complexion Make Myself Clear Makeup
reviews-text: I have insanely oily, acne-prone skin. I tried other foundations including expensive ones from designer brands and then I found this gem. When I have breakouts, the salicylic acid helps to clear them up and they appear less red/inflamed when I take off my makeup at the end of the day. I haven't noticed a difference in preventing breakouts using this foundation, but I wasn't concerned about that. I use a beauty blender to apply and blend this foundation and it always looks incredible. The coverage is medium but buildable and has a soft matte finish. I don't notice it sliding off my face even when I don't use a foundation primer with my oily skin and I've gone 18 hours without touching up or reapplying. I will continue to re-purchase this foundation again and again regardless of whether or not I continue to have issues with acne. Almay, please do not discontinue this or make major formula changes!

name: BAREPRO Performance Wear Powder Foundation
reviews-text:
Skin type: Oily 
Shade: Sandstone

I purchased this on a whim at the end of last year because it was on sale. I don't normally wear foundation every day (liquid ones are usually too heavy and take too much time in the mornings) and wanted something that would be light, easy to apply, and would sit well with my very oily skin. It's spring now and after multiple uses I can honestly say I love this foundation. It applies on powdery and then melts in nicely with my skin and gives a skin like finish. I have not experienced any caking so far. I also apply my Laura Mercier setting powder under my eyes and t zone areas to help control oil. I've received several compliments on how good and natural it looks.

name: Say What?! Foundation
reviews-text: I have very dry skin. No matter what primer I used or how much I moisturized, foundations (even "hydrating" ones) would ALWAYS make me look dry and cakey. I finally gave this foundation a try, and I absolutely fell in love! With my favorite moisturizer and primer, this foundation makes my skin look smooth and flawless! I can also build it up without it appearing cakey. Even around the usual places, like the area around my nose. It also doesn't settle into my fine lines, wrinkles, or even my pores. If you have dry skin, I highly recommend this foundation!

name: CC+ Cream Illumination SPF 50+
reviews-text: Beyond happy with this. First time trying this brand and I'm sooo glad I did. I have horrible combination skin; large pores and redness/acne with skin ranging from super dry to super oily. This foundation has the perfect amount of coverage for me. I didn't even use a primer and this made my pores disappear. It feels light and moisturizing on the skin. I haven't have a problem with creasing or drying like I've experienced with other foundations. Some 'illuminating' foundations are oily looking but this one gives you the perfect soft glow. Haven't had an issue with it transferring or fading either. I wore it to bed on accident one night and I woke up and it still looked freshly applied. Will definitely buy again.

name: Skin Love Weightless Blur Foundation
reviews-text:
I absolutely love this foundation. I used Urban Decay's Naked Skin for a long time until they changed the formula and it was really hard to find a new foundation that works for me. I have pale skin with extreme pink undertones and most foundations are just too neutral or yellow toned to work for me. Not this one! It goes on perfectly and I don't have to worry about it looking unnatural on my skin! It covers my rosacea and helps me feel confident again. All I need is 1-2 squirts of product and it spreads all over my face! It's also not super matte, so it dries, but doesn't look cakey. Gives me a nice, glowing look. 

I only have a one real con (hence the 4 star instead of 5 star rating): The price. This foundation is really expensive especially for how little is in the bottle. I'm having to replace foundations once every 2-3 months, when I used to be able to go at least 4-ish months with my older foundations.The squirt bottle is great, but once you start running low, it becomes very difficult to actually get the product out and you have to start rolling it up (like a toothpaste bottle). I wish there were an easier way to remove the top so that you could get the rest of the product out. For the price, I would expect this to last a little longer. My only other con is that if your skin is dry, it clings to the dry patches. I have rosacea on my face so I suffer from a lot of cheek dryness and texture patches and if I'm having a flare up, this foundation just clings to it and makes it more obvious.

name: Dream Radiant Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: Light coverage, doesn't really soak in well and therefore takes a while to apply and properly set and I find it breaks up on my skin by the 5 hr mark. It's not good for me as far as coverage and lasting power goes but my skin seems to like it so I've been applying it with my fingers or wet beauty blender after my morning skincare routine on days I don't really do a full face or care much about coverage. I'm acne prone with dry skin and it doesn't irritate my skin or clog pores. I don't hate it enough not to use it, but I still expect more from this.

name: Skin Illusion Natural Hydrating Foundation
reviews-text: This first thing I HAVE to say about this foundation is I LOVE the way it wears through out the day. It doesn't just "come off" in areas, like around the mouth & nose, but more like "absorbs away". After several hours(6hrs+) my foundation still look great, skin tone evened out. But it's at this point when it starts to "fade". It's a very gradual fade, kind of like when you start to lose your summer tan, it fades evenly. Even after 14hrs I STILL have tone evening coverage without patches. This stuff has changed my game, as I was starting to get absolutely sick of trying different foundations to get that truly natural looking finish that doesn't have "shimmer" or specks of "glimmer/glitter" like so many dewy type foundations have. Foundations I looked at where either really good for the first hour, but then dried out after an hour or two, or felt super heavy & then settled harshly into my wrinkles and lines... This stuff is neither. It has a watery like consistency that floats on to skin & blends so easily it's like watching magic happen! Let's face it, almost ALL foundations settle into wrinkles, it WILL happen. The difference between foundations is how easily it can be corrected and how many times you'll have to correct it before it stays in its permanent spot, if at all. After allowing it dry down for about 20 minutes there might be a couple areas that have slight settling, this is sooo easy to fix with just the touch/press of a finger. Areas like the forehead with lines/wrinkles just lightly press in (once you learn your problem areas it helps to do this from the beginning). If you have settling under the eye, gently swipe your finger downwards (opposite direction in which the line runs). After you've corrected the settled areas, most with a hydrating setting spray. This enhances the natural/ slightly dewy finish. If you have oily skin, this really isn't for you and I don't recommend ruining the gorgeous natural finish this foundation has by putting powder over it
review-keyword: Dry skin? THIS. IS. YOUR. HOLY. GRAIL!!!

reviews-text: Ulta, please, please, please bring this wonderful Mineral Foundation back! We both love everything about your mineral products, including the setting powder and mineral blush. I have had to explain that this product was discontinued to 3 friends who are addicted to these mineral foundations thanks to me. I have now tried and switched to many Ulta products from the expensive name brands not only because the are so much more affordable but because they are superior products. product-links: Futurist Hydra Rescue Moisturizing Makeup SPF 45
name: Futurist Hydra Rescue Moisturizing Makeup SPF 45
reviews-text: Since I have bit my mid-30s, my skin tone has evened out and started getting dryer vs oily, I have been looking for something that offer hydration and coverage. However, since I'm also starting to see the ever so slight fine lines, I feel that most full coverage foundations only make them look that much more obvious. This is where Futurist Hydra Rescue comes in! It's a beautifully moisturizing make up AND offers the perfect amount of coverage while feeling light and looking like a better version of my own skin. The coverage is buildable, so it would work for those evenings out also!

reviews-text: I saw on YouTube that this was high coverage and they weren't kidding! I have oily, acne prone skin, and I'm used to wearing liquid foundation, plus powder foundation that would have to reapply throughout the day. This I can wear alone, covers everything beautifully, and I don't feel like I'm wearing pounds of makeup. The provided applicator works great, and then I used a brush to blend blush/bronzer on top. Hours later I still didn't look shiny and it washes off easy too. Can't wait for this to be back in stock!

reviews-text: I started using this brand about a month ago, and I love it. I have sensitive skin and rosacea, and their foundation and primer are miracle products in my opinion. I decided to try this to cover up some bruises on my arms for a holiday party, and I was blown away at how well this it works. I tried it on my legs just for fun, and they look airbrushed. It's better than self tanner! I would recommend using as little as possible just enough to get even coverage. You will likely have to use a very soft, dry cloth to wipe off the layer of powder once it dries. It will get on fabric, but it comes right out when washed. Great product if you need to cover up blemishes or imperfections for a special event, or just to wear something that shows some skin.

reviews-text:

I also can't use the clinique moisturizer prior to this foundation because they don't mix. 
overall it's an ok foundation but I'm not purchasing it again.

reviews-text: I'm not really the type of person who wears foundation everyday. After buying and trying this product I wore foundation everyday for 3 weeks straight. It looks beautiful on the skin and give a light to medium coverage. I personally don't set this foundation and it looks very skin like. It doesn't have a super incredible wear time. On me it typically wear about 6 hours before going down hill. I would definitely recommend this foundation to my dry skin friends. It is my favorite foundation currently.

reviews-text:

Under the foundation, I like to use some kind of primer or moisturizer. I tried Pacifica's sea and C love serum, and it works great under this foundation.  

Since ordering this foundation and serum, I've thrown out my other silicone-based foundations and primer.  

Very pleased with the products, and highly recommend.

As someone with fair-to-light skin that needs a foundation with a bit more yellow in it (but NOT orange!) to even me out, this fits the bill. The shade "Fair" is light in color, but doesn't give me that ghostly "too fair" look. Using a sponge, it is buildable (which is something I need as I have red spots everywhere), and it LOOKS LIKE SKIN. 
As someone who has tried just about every line to find a shade and formula that works for me, I am VERY happy to find it in a lower-priced foundation.  Bonus!

I hope they never stop making this wonderful makeup...it's superb!!

reviews-text:
I have loved Morphe products before but this one was such a flop. Just save your money.

For reference I have combo skin:  It is a very matte foundation and clings to all those spots you DON'T want it too. Made my skin look textured, dry, and cakey. Throughout the day it loses the matte effect and then is a little bit oily. The foundation does not wear well at all. I feel like it breaks-up/separates on my skin and looks so messy. 

I have tried to make this work in every way possible- different applicators, primers, setting sprays, powders and there is NO saving this. In my opinion, it is just not worth the money. 

My main issue is with the performance but I'd note that there is also an odor- seriously smells like acrylic paint from the craft store.

reviews-text: Was very disappointed when they discontinued the original DWL foundation - it was my holy grail (especially in the Summer). The old formula wasn't nearly as matte. My skin feels and looks heavy once I add all my powders. I don't use glowy setting sprays but I'm considering buying one just so my face doesn't look dried out and dusty when using this foundation.
review-keyword: Not as good as the OG formula

name: Smooth Liquid Camo Foundation
reviews-text: I really wanted to love this foundation since I've heard such great things about Dermablend, but it did NOT work for me. Granted, I have very temperamental skin - dry but gets oily as the day goes on, with severe rosacea. But I found its thick consistency really hard to blend (even after warming it on my wrist) and after about four hours it was already wearing off my skin in patches. Plus, I was between two shades - the darker one was WAY too dark and the lighter one made me look like a ghost and made my rosacea spots look grey. (Cute, right?) Also, my face felt itchy after wearing it for about 20 minutes. I'm giving it three stars because it looked awesome when I swatched it - really bummed it didn't look that good when I put it on my whole face.

name: Luminous Foundation
reviews-text: This is the only foundation I have found that gives me the GLOW and the DEWY SKIN that I deserve!!!!! I have dry skin so the extra glow and moisture is welcome for me and it mixes fantastic with liquid glow products in the foundation and under it. I can definitely see why people with combo oily skin would not like this product as it could be a bit slippy on too much oil. However, because of my skin type I have not had that problem and the foundation lasts long for me! I would say it a true build able medium coverage. Like, that could not be more accurate. You can definitely build it up or even sheer it down. The ONLY reason I am giving it four stars instead of five is because the shade range is not properly labeled. I was shade-matched in store to 160C. Now, I am fair with neutral undertones and 160c is cool undertones. However, this is definitely a warmer shade than you would typically expect for a cool undertone, it is even too warm for me especially if I keep building it up. So, this leads me to believe there is some misinformation in the shade labeling and you are better off matching in store than ordering online. Other than that, I love this foundation!

reviews-text: I do theatre makeup, and some people don't own makeup so I was looking for a palette that would cover everyone, but that I could also possibly use if needed on a day to day basis. So, when I saw Nyx had brought out a semi-affordable option (overpriced for the drugstore imo) I was so excited and tried it out quickly. However, this product looked horrible on the skin! The initial application looks very greasy, but its a cream product so I wasn't that worried. I put on my normal concealer then set with my normal powder. Initially from where I was standing it looked alright, but as I went through the rest of my makeup routine it just looked more and more awful. My pores looked huge. My smile lines were so prominent, and I'm a teenager so I don't really have any. Then the foundation just disappeared above my lip and in spots on my nose. When I was done and taking it off, it took so much micellar water to remove all the makeup from my pores that i'm scared there's some left and I'm gonna break out tomorrow. Def would not recommend

reviews-text: I saw these online and wondered why they were not already in the foundation package. I love to mix shades throughout the year, and this will allow for that with even better results.  The only value that I can see to not adding them to the foundation package is so that you reuse them with each new bottle, rather than throwing the pumps away with the glass bottles.  Its a one time $10 investment, which will pay for itself (my opinion) in one or two bottles based on what I see going down the drain as I wash off my hands.

I live in New Mexico and Texas and in Texas the heat and humidity was terrible yet the product held up, till I removed it at night. I can not purchase another product as good.

I see how that may be inconvenient for some but it's worth extra few seconds. It Stays on and covers without being too heavy when mixed in. I love beauty product and am constantly trying new ones but this is something I always reach for.

reviews-text: So I was looking for a liquid or cream foundation to give me a dewy look. I found this and it happened to be on sale in store. I bought the lightest color you can get and it just turned a lighter orange or tan. My skin is pale or porcelain in some makeup cases. I had to go all day looking like I came from the bakery. Now I'm not totally knocking this foundation. It just wasn't for me. This is a good quality product. It goes on smooth, feels nice and creamy, it doesn't settle, or pronounce your pours. It didn't feel like I had anything on my face and blended well. It also did give a beautiful dewy look. I recommend it it if these are things you're looking for and for people with tan skin.

name: Say What?! Foundation
reviews-text:
I'm really sad that this didn't work. I love supporting indie/upcoming brands. I had to find my shade on Uoma's website, since it's more in depth on getting your right shade, and I couldn't try it in person since none of the stores in my area have it. ULTA, you need to put indie/upcoming brands in MORE stores, and not just in select few California stores!
The consistency is SUPER watery. 4-5 pumps needed on my brush to make coverage on half of my face. Those 4-5 pumps is what I also needed to have it sit on top of the bristles and not sink down to the middle of the bristles. With a sponge, it was gone. It was also tricky to apply nice and even without brush or sponge marks. Even with matching online, the foundation was still a bit yellow (I have T2C which should be for fair pink) and then it oxidized orange. And the fragrance! Oh dear. It never goes away and irritated my eyes so much, and I didn't bring it up super close to my eye area! And the smell doesn't go away! I also have oily skin, but with it being winter it's more combo-oily, and it felt noticeably dry. You definitely have to set it with translucent powder. It does not fully dry down on its own.I will say, it was very lightweight, even with 2 layers on. I know that sounds confusing, being I just said it's lightweight, but it's true. The packaging is very lux feeling, minus the cap. Those last two factors helped give it a 2 star instead of 1 Star.
If you can get your shade, you want coverage that you can truly choose how much you want, you can make it work, and have really oily skin, I think this would work for you.

reviews-text: I've struggled for years trying to find the right foundation for my skin. I have watched so many tutorials on how to apply foundation with different tools, I have read reviews and took many skin quizzes, and nothing seemed to work. I was wearing Urban Decay's Naked All-Nighter foundation for years.... because every time I went into Ulta, it was "highly recommended" (which honestly felt more like an advertisement rather than a personal recommendation), but finally I had enough and went in there one day and asked could I please have a more personalized recommendation for foundation because Urban Decay's foundation kept "oxidizing" and turning orange on my skin, making it not match my neck. A very nice Ulta rep came and helped me find the right shade and she recommended the Amazonian Clay... needless to say I've been hooked ever since! I also bought the Tarte brush to go with it because it was soooo soft and applied so much better than a normal brush/sponge. Love this foundation! So happy I finally found something to match my skin tone and doesn't turn orange!

Since it's water based I would avoid using a sponge because it soaks up a lot of the product. I prefer to use a brush instead.

I wouldn't recommend putting a silicone based primer on before hand because it may ball up the product. I just put on some silicone free moisturizer and it goes on great.

It wears beautifully throughout the day and I notice it just evening out my skin tone without completely covering my freckles or making them look like I tried to cover them up and failed.

It's my go to everyday light makeup foundation and i love it.

reviews-text: I have a quarter size dark red scar on my leg from having surgery to remove a freckly and tried using under eye concealers to cover up but they just rubbed off.  Then I found this.  Once you get the right color and use a setting powder, it last all day - is water proof and does not rub off during the day.  You cannot even tell I have a scar that is covered up.

name: Quick Fix Body Foundation Stick
reviews-text: I have melasma on the side of my cheeks and forehead. Nothing covers it completely except MAC's full coverage concealer but the container is so small so I was buying the concealer in the large compact called their full coverage foundation which is only available online and requires a brush or sponge to apply. Now, I buy this stick and just dab it on, pat down with a beauty blender and set with a good setting powder and it lasts all day and looks flawless. I use a foundation underneath and then this on top to make it blend out nicely but I suspect you do not even need the foundation underneath.  I LOVE this product!! Thank you Dermablend!
review-keyword: This is a must have produce for melasma!!!

name: Perfect Lasting Foundation
reviews-text: I don't know what it is about this formula but it just don't want to blend/build an even layer on my face; it just moves around and around and leaves streaks all over, whether I apply it with a brush, sponge or fingers. I've used it with 3 different primers, no primer, clean face etc etc but it just does not work for me. I'm really disappointed because I was looking for a foundation that was more moisturizing for the winter (I have combination skin but it gets dryer in winter) and this foundation had really good reviews but it just didn't come through for me. Honestly, this is one of the worst foundations I've used in a really long time.

name: Power Play Foundation
reviews-text:
Im about an NC30 in mac, and wheat/and ivory beige in estee lauder double wear, Punjab in Nars sheer glow. 
I got a g40( not g40+) in this and it was a pretty good match. It dries quickly during appication, so u have to work fast. The finish is really pretty. Its matt but makes your skin look more blurred versus a flat matt look. It photographed really well. 

I have olive skin that gets very oily so i dont know how   this would work on dry skin? It may cling to patches. 

After about 3 to 4 hrs in (of me sitting at my work desk) my oils broke through. I tried for 2 more days, and the same happened.  i use a light,  non oily moisturizer applied 30 minutes before foundation application. 

The foundation looks beautiful first 3 to 4 hrs, but it did not last on my skin. Ive tried TONS of foundations (nars, mac,  dose of colors, lancome ) and the one that always lasts on my oily skin is estee lauder double wear.

reviews-text: Was looking for a healthier foundation/ tinted moisturizer option and tried this. I am very fair but with alot of pink undertone and I got the color fair and its PERFECT. Has a pretty natural dewy look to it. I usually use IT cosmetics CC cream which does have a little bit more coverage but might just start using this instead for a light natural makeup look. The only con is it feels like theres like little crystals in it which just feels strange and you can see them on your hands after applying. But overall it's good and will buy again.

name: Dream Tint Tinted Moisturizer
reviews-text: This was a little more sheer than I had hoped it would be (probably because I got the lightest shade) but honestly I was very surprised at how my skin looked. It really just evened my skin out and gave me a really pretty no makeup makeup look. Not to mention my skin was literally GLOWING. The feeling of this product on your face is very lightweight and airy and almost feels just like putting a regular moisturizer on. It is a little tacky though. I suggest hitting it with a little powder and you're good to go. This is my new favorite tinted moisturizer!!

name: Pro Matte Mixing Pigment
reviews-text: I had been wanting to try the It Cosmetics CC Cream forever but never bought it because I'm very pale and their lightest shade is ridiculously dark. I happened to see this on sale last week and got the white one and a travel size of the CC Cream to try it out, and it worked beautifully. It mixed it into my perfect shade and it didn't change the consistency or the finish of the foundation, I am so happy to have this product, I want to get a dozen backups.

name: Beyond Perfecting Foundation + Concealer
reviews-text: I was looking for the perfect winter shade for my ghostly white skin. (Please summer hurry up). I went to ULTA a few weeks back and this color was out of stock. I signed up for email and I got an email that it arrived!!!! I was pumped. I ordered, it came in a timely fashion and I have worn it nearly every day. I put this on with a beauty blender and shazammm! Perfecto makeup!

The shade options were really great and it was good coverage for the lightweight feel. It would be fine for a dewy look but I wanted matte.

name: Firm Flesh Thickstick Foundation
reviews-text: This product is amazing! In my opinion, if you are more of a natural beauty lover like myself, GET THIS! This is one of the few foundations I've tried that resembles actual skin and dosent look like your wearing something. It's like your skin but better. It has a sheen that isnt necessary dewy but resembles the natural shine your skin has. It is thin, smooth, a bit sheer but is buildable without getting thick sticky or cakey. This isnt for someone looking for a full beat. I reccomend this to pretty much everyone as it is now my holy grail foundation. You dont need much at all to get decent coverage either. One small swipe on each cheekbone, across the forehead and the bridge of the nose. Blend it down and inwards and itll look like a better version of you. I am going to purchase another color in the future to use as a contour stick. Also, dont use a wet or dry beauty blender with this. Itll get streaky. This is made to be used with a foundation brush. All in all I think this is a permanent fixture in my makeup bag! And the shade range is fantastic! What have you go to lose? Buy it!!!!

It's cakey, is not sheer at all and it gets on everythin and makes every flaw stand out (or makes you realize you have flaws that you didn't see before). Such a disappointment to see the old formula thrown out. If people want cakey thick foundation then this is for you but if want something sheer and dewy you'll need to look elsewhere unfortunately, like I have. I still haven't been able to find anything comparable. Please bring back the old formula.

name: Dream Urban Cover Flawless Coverage Foundation SPF 50
reviews-text: I have bad acne scars and redness and it very slightly covered it up. The finish is dewy which I like, it's just sooo sheer. Even when I build it up, it still barely shows up. It doesn't look bad on the skin however, it hid my pores pretty well and the finish was nice. It hid my redness but not the acne/scars. The coverage is definitely that of a BB/CC cream in my opinion and would definitely look better on someone who doesn't need much for their skin and is going for a more natural look. It also doesn't last that long even with trusted primer/powder/setting spray. Definitely something you would just put on for a super natural touch up. Overall 3 stars just because the coverage and longevity isn't there.

product-links: Your Skin But Better CC+ Airbrush Perfecting Powder
name: Your Skin But Better CC+ Airbrush Perfecting Powder
reviews-text:
This is the very first line of the ingredients:
Active: Titanium Dioxide, Zinc Oxide

I copied and pasted from the ingredient list above and checked other sites to make sure it wasn't a mistake. Those are BOTH sunscreens, the SAME sunscreens that have been in this product for years. I'm not sure why the packaging changed but the product is still the goods.
The powder itself is great for extra coverage. It fits between a regular light coverage setting powder and a powder foundation. I don't think you could get the kind of coverage they are showing in the promo pics without a lot ... and I do mean a lot of layers. It would be a powder pile on disaster! For example; I apply with a large puffy powder brush when I want to get a little more coverage out of a tinted moisturizer or the it Cc cream. When I'm touching up and topping off my SPF during the day I use the puff or a denser brush. I keep a small face mist in my bag because it's thick ( sunscreen drawback ) and when using this way unless you give it some moisture it's going to be a noticeably heavy powder look. Not cakey, just noticeably heavy. It does add to coverage but there's no way it is going to give full coverage or even medium. 
Their Celebration foundation ( the illumination version is fantastic ) is a great option if you want a powder foundation. The CC powder isn't a foundation and I'm puzzled why they are marketing it that way since it will only lead to disappointed customers. 
If you want additional coverage or need an easy way to bump up your SPF throughout the day this is a really nice powder.

I switched to a foundation brush, which was a bit of an adjustment for me, but it works wonderfully with the Liquid Minerals (Radiant) foundation. name: PHYTO-PIGMENTS Flawless Serum Foundation
reviews-text:
Organic food ingredients are often not good skincare, especially if the ingredients are citrus plant derivatives (this contains at least one) with the exception of vitamin C. For around the price of this smelly fruit skin stressor there are elegant and properly preserved foundations from luxury brands. (Preservatives keep foundations from going bad and have been tested. "Clean" makeup is a gimmick that causes you to need to throw things out sooner and buy more!)

The color that I was shade matched with had a gray cast on me, shade 8. I tried to point this out, but before I knew it, the sales person had put the box in my hand and was done with me even though I clearly didn't like it. She knew better for my "dry and mature skin" - her words! I'm 43, and it's winter so that might be accurate but be nicer about it!  I could not buy this stinking gray foundation that contains sensitizing plant ingredients. Some items from this brand smell more like fruity wood polish than makeup and I've thrown them out because of their high fragrance.
review-keyword: "Clean" often means sensitizing and fast spoiling!

name: SuperStay Full Coverage Powder Foundation
reviews-text:
I've been wanting to switch over to powder foundations for a while now, because I'm honestly sick of using liquid/BB creams, and I love the ease of quickly powdering your face and being ready to go. 

When I first applied this, I was SUPER impressed with how full coverage it is. That is one of the main reasons I will continue to keep trying this out, because I love the coverage and the finish. I think it was a great start to powder foundations for me. 

However, it made me really oily within a few hours. I'm not sure if that's powder foundation in general for me (I haven't tried many yet), because I do tend to be an oily person. I just really wish this wouldn't make me so oily, because I really like the product otherwise. But, for the price and the coverage, it's not too bad of a deal! 
Bottom line: I probably wouldn't expect this to last all day on your skin, unless you have fairly normal skin!

reviews-text:
Love this stuff! It's my new go-to foundation for face and body. Covers up dark eye circles, acne, and freckles on my arms amazingly. Matches my skin tone, amazing coverage and pigmentation. It's hard enough to find a foundation for porcelain skin, even harder to find a quality one that actually covers and doesn't oxidize. I was woefully disappointed by Two Faced full coverage foundation in Cloud after it matched me but didn't cover well at all and left my skin feeling wet. As long as you blend well and set, this won't crease, as with most foundations, but heavier applications in places such as under the eyes may crease.
This makeup is definitely heavy in pigmentation, but also in weight and feel. Great for oily/combination skin but dry skin or light makeup users might not enjoy. Be careful what powders you use or it may turn color, but an otherwise fantastic product I will buy again and again.

name: Conceal & Define Full Coverage Foundation
reviews-text: My search for a foundation for my combination skin felt like a most fruitless endeavor. My large pores just loved to magnify the moment foundation touched my face. This held true even when using Fenty or MAC foundations. I happened upon this foundation one day while perusing the store and found a shade that perfectly matched (another struggle I had failed at more often than not). At the price point, this felt like a gamble I would be stupid not to take. After the first use, I thought surely this was a joke; how could this drugstore-priced foundation far exceed the results of makeup triple this price? But it isn't a joke and months later, my skin is still in love with this product. It has never made me break out; it doesn't flake or congeal as the day wears on; it covers my imperfections with ease; it works in tandem with every primer I've used with it. The bottle is large and lasted several months, even with usage at least 5 days a week. The doe-foot applicator is ideal for putting the product directly onto the skin and for minimizing any unnecessary waste of makeup. It's mattifying without being too drying, yet allows for a glowing, dewy appearance at certain angles. It's the best of both worlds. It doesn't fill my pores quite like I'd like, but my primer is now responsible for that. I don't think there is any foundation out there that will address my personal crater-sized pores. I've bought this a few times now to keep handy (and shade-match for the summertime) and between its effectiveness as a foundation and the price, there is no competition.

reviews-text: I am convinced that any glowing, positive reviews on this product have to have been submitted by people who work for EL. We all agree that this new formula is not only not improved, but it's really bad.  It does not go on evenly, it dries on in patches.  I am not a fan of the finish either.  It's too matte and makes my skin look dry.  The past year has been nothing but me buying and trying various foundations to find one I like as well as the old formula and so far, not one of them has come close.  It has been extremely frustrating.  I tried a few other EL foundations and I haven't loved those either.  My friends who used the original have also moved on to other brands and haven't found one they like as well..  My quest for the original DWL replacement continues...  If they would bring back the original, I would HAPPILY pay twice the price (or even more), but I will not be buying this one again.

name: Smooth Liquid Camo Foundation
reviews-text: I really wanted this foundation to work. Regardless of what setting spray, primer, powder I use to set, it literally wipes right off. It makes my skin very oily as the day goes on. It just doesn't set well.

name: Mattifying Powder Foundation
reviews-text: I used to be a die-hard liquid foundation user, as every mineral/powder foundation I tried made me break out like crazy. However, I was looking for something with a lighter feel and coverage that was quick to apply, and this product is IT! So easy to apply and provides just enough coverage to even out my skin tone without looking cakey or creasing like liquid foundation. I have yet to see any breakouts after 1 week of wearing. I have very light skin but went for the shade "sand", as I get tanner in the summer. The color is a perfect match for my light skin and I may have to buy an even darker one for when tan, so I would definitely recommend going darker in color choice.

name: CC+ Cream Illumination SPF 50+
reviews-text: I got this as my first non-drugstore foundation so I was really disappointed that the Silver paint on the tube started coming off in just a couple uses. This lead to silver flicks on my face I'd have to pick off. The cream itself is okay but I didn't see anything to justify the price difference between my Maybelline normal cream and it. It was also heavier than what I was looking for. I won't be buying it again.

name: PurePressed Base Mineral Foundation Refill
reviews-text: My skin looks flawless and feels amazing wearing the Radiant PurePressed Base. I have been using it for several years now. Using the hydration spray to set it is key.

name: Super Stay Full Coverage Foundation
reviews-text: This foundation is not full coverage. I'd say medium. If you have oily skin this isn't too great. It looked great when I put it on, but after a few hours it started to look patchy and oily. Doesn't last long at all! However, doesn't look cakey.

product-links: Double Duty Beauty Shape Tape Pressed Powder
name: Double Duty Beauty Shape Tape Pressed Powder
reviews-text: I was hoping for a bit more coverage since the product is billed as light/medium. I would say it falls solidly inside "light coverage." That being said, the application is smooth and it blurs minor imperfections nicely. Not great for covering uneven skin tone but nice for a little coverage.

name: Pro Coverage Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: I decided to give this foundation a try since it didn't break the bank and had some good reviews. It goes well on my skin but it is quite thin like cheap paint. It says "pro coverage" on the bottle but definitely doesn't live up to its name.

name: ColorStay Full Cover Foundation
reviews-text: This is a great full coverage foundation at a great price. Covers all my imperfections!

name: Studio Fix Powder Plus Foundation
reviews-text: This product is a repurchase. Second time ordering this item, and I love it.

name: Beyond Perfecting Powder Foundation + Concealer
reviews-text: I usually do not like putting foundation on because i feel it on my face and continue to rub my face through out the day.  I do not have that issue with this foundation.  It glides on so smoothly.  I wouldn't say its a full coverage because it lets my freckles still come through, but i like to be as natural as possible.  It gives me just  what a need, even skin tone, smooth skin and a clean looking face.

product-links: True Match Lumi Healthy Luminous Makeup
name: True Match Lumi Healthy Luminous Makeup
reviews-text: good coverage

name: Infallible Pro-Glow Foundation
reviews-text: It works great on my oily skin, leaves a healthy. Usually I gravitate to matte products but the pro glow works so good! It has definitely changed my mind. I think I've finally found my go-to. It's also definitely full coverage which I love.
review-keyword: Love this product it works great even on my oily skin.

product-links: Complexion Rescue Hydrating Foundation Stick Broad Spectrum SPF 25
name: Complexion Rescue Hydrating Foundation Stick Broad Spectrum SPF 25
reviews-text: Love this product.  On me anyway, has a glowy look and I love it.  I've used it with a brush, a sponge, and my fingers.  Don't recommend the brush.  With the sponge and my fingers it goes on neatly and looks great.  Highly recommend!
review-keyword: Gives me a Lit from Within glow!

name: Pro Longwear Nourishing Waterproof Foundation
reviews-text: for the price it should do at least one thing that it claims. at first it looks nice so maybe ok for photo shoot..

product-links: Sheer Line Of Defense Foundation SPF 30
name: Sheer Line Of Defense Foundation SPF 30
top-negative-review: This clung so weirdly to my face. I made sure to give it a fair chance and try it different ways, but no matter what I did, this looked awful. It would be patchy and have coverage in one area and then no coverage in another area. It was the most bizarre experience I've ever had with foundation and I...

name: Simply Ageless 3-in-1 Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: Too oily...bad color

name: Pro.Matte Foundation
reviews-text: I bought this foundation because the reviews seemed great for the most part. I was fooled, I did not like this foundation one bit. At first I thought it was just that I bought the wrong shade, so I bought another shade. I don't like either, I wish I could pinpoint exactly what is the problem. I will wait return these two and see if there is a different shade. I've used them a few times now and it's just a no for me. I do like that it's not heavy on the skin, so that's a plus.

product-links: Complexion Rescue Tinted Hydrating Gel Cream Broad Spectrum SPF 30
name: Complexion Rescue Tinted Hydrating Gel Cream Broad Spectrum SPF 30
top-negative-review: I really, really wanted to love this product.  I've worn BM powder (original) for years and years, and it's the only makeup that doesn't cause breakouts.  Full disclosure, I have very acne prone skin, and I can tell within just a few days if a product is going to exacerbate my acne. This product did...

product-links: Clear Complexion Make Myself Clear Makeup
name: Clear Complexion Make Myself Clear Makeup
reviews-text: I love this foundation! I have combination skin but mostly towards the oily side and this foundation along with the Almay loose finishing powder to set helps my skin stay oil free all day! It helped me clear my breakouts while wearing makeup. I struggled so much with finding a foundation for me and this one has helped me a lot. It does dry out your skin but wear your moisturizer before makeup and after taking off your makeup and you will be good and your makeup will look flawless.

name: Sheer Glow Foundation
reviews-text: Not worth the price. it's a medium coverage, its buildable but it doesnt sit well on my dry sensitive skin. Even adding farsali drops and moisturizing before it just ends up patchy. very thick formula. not worth the $$ in my opinion based off my skin.

name: HD Liquid Coverage Foundation
reviews-text: I am super picky with foundations and this is the first foundation in a long time that I love! It doesn't look look cakey and lasts all day looking natural. It's amazing! I highly recommend trying this out. I found that less is more with this one though. Start with a little bit and then build up coverage as needed.

product-links: Complexion Rescue Tinted Hydrating Gel Cream Broad Spectrum SPF 30
name: Complexion Rescue Tinted Hydrating Gel Cream Broad Spectrum SPF 30
top-positive-review: My new go-to!

product-links: Skin Feels Good Hydrating Skin Tint
name: Skin Feels Good Hydrating Skin Tint
reviews-text: All I wanted was a nice tinted moisturizer with SPF and I found the perfect one! The coverage is light, but can be buildable. Could be a tinted moisturizer or add more and make it a light covered foundation. It smells very perfume-y but I love the smell. I recommend this for anyone who wants an everyday light coverage tinted moisturizer.

name: Flawless Lumière Radiance-Perfecting Foundation
reviews-text: This has fantastic coverage without looking heavy or matte, but it's not excessively dewy either. I have dry, mature skin and on me this is a satin finish. It lasts well throughout the day, doesn't cling to dry patches, looks good over texture, and I love that it has zero fragrance and no drying alcohol in it. Beautiful packaging, very classy like all Laura Mercier products. I'm an NC15-20 and Cashew is a great match for me. I'm super excited Ulta is carrying this brand now- I was able to check it all out in-store! I highly recommend if you have dryer skin and like good coverage- it's beautiful!

name: Pro.Matte Foundation
reviews-text: I bought two different shades. Both shades seemed to have something wrong with them. They would not mix in the bottles like the formula was separated. It would not blend out in my skin at all. I didn't even try to wear it out of the house. I tried mixing it with other more expensive foundations, nope. Nothing worked. This is a horrible foundation. What a waste of money, so disappointed. There are better cheaper foundations don't waste your money on this one.

name: Leg and Body Makeup
reviews-text: I was in store so excited when I found this product that I can cover up some unwanted dark scars for work. However when I had put this on no matter what I did even though I had the perfect color I tried primers I tried setting powder setting sprays hair spray this product transferred on everything no matter what I was wearing it just kept coming off and getting onto my clothes or even on the counter that I would work out for my job. Very disappointing. I possibly got a bad batch but this was definitely a let down.

name: BH Liquid Foundation - Naturally Flawless
reviews-text: I love this foundation! A little goes a looong way. Can be full coverage, a little on the heavy side since its a thick consistency but this is def my go-to foundation at the moment.

name: Natural Radiant Longwear Foundation
reviews-text: I have been stuck on MAC studio fix for years. I just tried this foundation and i am very impressed! Takes no effort to blend into the skin!

name: Clean Fresh Skin Milk Foundation
reviews-text: I'm so upset with this foundation. I had good hopes for it. I purchased it the last day ulta was open. Now I can't return it, and when stores open up again I won't be able to anymore. It might be cheap, but I certainly do not recommend to anyone. Its patchy and I've found little clumps in mine. Not to mention the terrible smell.

name: Pro Foundation Palette
reviews-text: I started to contour my face very recently and I wanted to try on the contour palette which would be creamy. It surprised me a lot, how it is easy to use and contour your face, if you put too much of a dark tone, you can modify it with a light shade, or vice versa. I really recommend this to both - beginners and professionals.

name: Ultimate Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
top-positive-review: IT DEFIENTLY LASTS 24 HOURS

name: Photo Focus Dewy Foundation
reviews-text: I have normal to dry skin so dewy/luminous foundations are usually what I go for. This foundation looks beautiful when first applied to the skin, however it does not last long on my skin at all. By the 6th hour it looks very blotchy and broken up on my skin.

product-links: Sheer Line Of Defense Foundation SPF 30
name: Sheer Line Of Defense Foundation SPF 30
reviews-text: This has avery strong fragrance and is burning my face. My face is itchy. The coverage is terrible.

name: Cover Creme Full Coverage Foundation
reviews-text:
I have sensitive skin with eczema flare-ups 
This makeup, though initial good coverage, irritated my skin, and never truly "sets" - even with their setting powder - it transfers to my clothes and only lasts a few hours.
I went to this from Estée Lauder DW, hoping for a better coverage long wear product — this is not it.

product-links: No Makeup Foundation Serum Broad Spectrum SPF 20
name: No Makeup Foundation Serum Broad Spectrum SPF 20
reviews-text: When I received the last Foundation Serum I noticed that the new brand is not the same as the previous color that I had ordered last time.  I talked with the Perricone Customer service representative Maura who was a pleasure to work with.  Not only was she able to get me the correct shade; She was able to make some great suggestions about blending my current foundation serum.  This works perfectly as we will be heading to summer and my complexion gets darker even though I try to avoid the sun. It is nice that I can always rely on the excellence of Perricone products to provide flawless coverage as well as consistent positive customer service.

name: Super Stay Full Coverage Foundation
reviews-text: I was hesitant with this at first but it performs so well! It doesn't sit or stick to any areas and also pairs well with other products. New go to!

name: Goodness Glows Tinted Moisturizer
reviews-text: It saves me alot of time in the mornings and my skin looks great :)

name: Conceal & Define Full Coverage Foundation
reviews-text: honestly, i waited to leave a review to really see if i noticed drawbacks to the foundation. It is a full coverage, MATTE foundation so a little goes a LONG WAY. I have dry skin and i have noticed no problem with the foundation and it matches my skin beautifully. i do mix it with a yellow corrector because the shade range is another issue, but I've had a worst issue with other brands

name: The Healthy Foundation SPF 20
reviews-text: I bought the LW2 foundation shade and when it came in. It looks 5x lighter than what it displayed as. So I was confused wonder if they ran out of what I ordered and just gave me something else and put the LW2 sticker on it to convince me to believe this is the foundation that I ordered. Well I tried it on, and for some reason when I put the foundation on and blended it with my skin, after a few minutes it literally matched my skin tone but it still a tad bit lighter (but highly even noticeable). Also it somewhat a cover up dark spots but not 100%. I'm probably gonna try a darker shade but this will have to do now sadly.

name: Aquasurance Compact Foundation
reviews-text: This is the best foundation I have ever tried. I own about 40 foundations and this is the best of all time. My skin is very fair and porcelain matches perfectly!! Also, my skin is on the drier side I would say and most foundations even dewy ones cling to areas like between my brows and look weird on my nose. This foundation is flawless. I use the sponge it comes with DRY and swipe on my face and then pat with a foundation brush to blend in a bit better if needed. I bought it while it was half off but it is no longer in stock- for a reason- I wish I stocked up. I don't want to use another foundation ever again. Coverage is so full and amazing. You put concealer on under your eyes or where needed first, then this powder and then contour and bronzer. Touch up whenever.. ..so simple as the sponge comes with!!! Amazing.

name: Celebration Full Coverage Powder Foundation
reviews-text: I am very disappointed in this powder. I will not be buying it again and I feel for the product it is very over priced.

product-links: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation
name: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation
reviews-text: I have been using this foundation/powder for years and will never turn back!

name: Skin Illusion Natural Hydrating Foundation
top-positive-review: New Favorite

product-links: Studio Skin Full Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
name: Studio Skin Full Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
top-positive-review: Ironically, I watched/read a bunch of reviews AFTER purchasing this foundation and NO ONE had anything good to say.... but I still gave it the benefit of the doubt and tried it and im glad I did. Every foundation works different for EVERY single person. Even ppl w/ the same skin type.  So after watc...

product-links: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation
name: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation
reviews-text: I'm not into coverage too much, so this product is really nice. It's also really quick and cuts my routine down by like 5 minutes. I use it as foundation I don't put it over anything besides primer and I think it works pretty well. It does move easier tho and loses its matte kinda fast. Regardless I still plan to use it in place of foundation for everyday/work.

name: Double Wear Stay-in-Place Makeup
reviews-text: ELDW, really is a product that works the hype. Great shade range, lovely finish, and can withstand various climates. I've warn it in dry Vegas heat, humid Florida sun, and in Colorado during the winter. If you're thinking about it- go for it. Keep it mind, this baby is 100 percent full coverage, and on the heavier side (not in a bad way.) But if that's not your jam, you may want to try something else- or Just shelf this one for certain occasions.

name: Double Wear Stay-in-Place Makeup
reviews-text: I have very oily skin and I like full coverage foundations. This is not all all full coverage and it broke up around my nose, chin and forehead within just a few hours. It also didn't help with oil absorption either.  My Maybelline Superstay foundation is WAY better and a lot less expensive.
review-keyword: Looks Good in the Beginning ONLY

product-links: Teint Idole Ultra Longwear Foundation Stick SPF 21
name: Teint Idole Ultra Longwear Foundation Stick SPF 21
reviews-text: I love this makeup. It is easy to apply and the color is perfect. I can also carry one in my purse.

name: Narcissist Foundation Stick
top-positive-review: One of the few clean foundations that I actually like, but still has some improvements to be had. It gives a light-medium buildable coverage that makes your skin glowy and radiant but doesn't overdo it. I have combo skin and this lasts pretty much your typical day without becoming greasy at the end ...

name: ColorStay Makeup For Normal/Dry Skin
top-negative-review: False Advertising

product-links: Studio Skin Full Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
name: Studio Skin Full Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
reviews-text: A little goes a long way! I'm so impressed with this and You get a lot of product for the price!

name: Olay Simply Ageless Foundation
reviews-text: I use this to cover up my imperfections and to look younger.  It has mousturer in the foundation so it helps to give you a young look.

name: Foundation Pump
reviews-text: Great little pump, perfect for liquid foundation. No more "ketchup bottle" problems! I can get just the right amount of foundation on my sponge with little effort. It turns to lock closed so it is travelable. I have also been using the extra little cover piece it comes with for traveling as extra protection, but so far no issues. Really makes my morning makeup routine faster and less messy.

name: Clean Fresh Skin Milk Foundation
reviews-text: It's my favorite cream but honestly it balls up in a weird way. I'm not sure if it's because I wet my sponge but it's not bad to where I hate the foundation. I have like 7 tubes and I would definitely recommend to a person who has patience.

product-links: Conceal & Define Satte Matte Powder Foundation
name: Conceal & Define Satte Matte Powder Foundation
reviews-text: My daughter and I have both switched to using more from this company it's a great makeup doesn't clog our pores and has great coverage

name: Bye Bye Foundation Powder
reviews-text: I have combination skin and a huge problem was finding a power that would set the foundation without having a flaky residue. Well, I found it! I was advised to use this only in the areas that I would need it and it's perfect! I recommend only using it in areas that you need it and find the correct shade because mines a slightly darker than desired so I have to use gracefully so I don't appear darker than what I am. A little goes a long way with this power and it creates an airbrushed finish in my opinion!
review-keyword: Great Setting Power | A Little Goes A Long Way

name: Like a Light Skin Tint
reviews-text: this product smells horrible has uneven coverage causes acne and is not verry long wearing.

product-links: Pretty Fresh Hyaluronic Acid Tinted Moisturizer
name: Pretty Fresh Hyaluronic Acid Tinted Moisturizer
reviews-text: This is the only foundation/tinted moisturizer that works for me! I have eczema and every other foundation or tinted moisturizer I've tried has shown a lot of texture on my skin but this one doesn't do that. Makes my skin look flawless and hydrated. Its light/medium coverage, I only use it to even out my skintone and cover up redness but it does that very well!
review-keyword: Only foundation/tinted moisturizer that works for me!

product-links: Born To Glow Naturally Radiant Foundation
name: Born To Glow Naturally Radiant Foundation

reviews-text: Once I started using this foundation my skin was starting to get patched dry spots, and then the acne started all over my face, and also neck area where I put foundation. Love the foundation itself, but I don't like that it made me have major acne I didn't have before using! If it didn't give me acne I would definitely recommend! It goes on light with great coverage without looking caked on
review-keyword: Gave me acne I never had Before!

name: PRO Soft Focus Longwear Foundation
top-negative-review: I have combo skin and not only did this dry me out but the color oxidizes a ton! I look orange wearing it because of the color it turns on my skin after 5 or so min. It also makes my skin feeling super dry throughout the day. Wouldn't recommend.

name: Clean Fresh Skin Milk Foundation
