I have had this for a month or two and I hate this. It barely changes your skin, but it has an extremely high price AND gets lines later in the day. It doesn't even show up on your skin. 
 I normally love nars, but this product was not it for me. HORRIBLE!

name: All Nighter Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: Coverage is ace, but the oxidation is insane.

name: ColorStay Makeup For Combo/Oily Skin
reviews-text: Last ALL day on my combo/oily skin. Doesn't even dry out my cheeks in the winter, which is a common problem for me. Buildable coverage, so you can either go for a more natural look or conceal all your sins! Shade range is kinda whack but 285 Shell (one of the new ones) is my best foundation match yet (NC20)

name: Goodness Glows Tinted Moisturizer
reviews-text: This product is great for "no makeup" makeup days. It tints my skin and felt very moisturizing. Smells wonderful. Not a lot of coverage (obviously) but when i used concealer over it, it blended out nicely. Looks great throughout the day and doesn't feel too heavy on my skin!

name: Flawless Finish Foundation
reviews-text: I really liked this foundation but it separates on my nose. I do have oily skin but this foundation won't set on my nose. But makes the rest of my face look really good.

name: Double Wear Stay-in-Place Makeup
top-positive-review: Best foundation EVER for oily skin!!!

name: Fast Base Stick Foundation
reviews-text: This is honestly an amazing product. I typically do my makeup on the go so this is so convenient to throw in my bag to take with me. It blends out well with my fingers and has pretty buildable coverage. I wouldn't use this on special occasions but is perfect for day to day use. It might not cover breakouts completely but definitely helps to even skin tone. Totally recommend for anyone trying out stick foundations for the first time. Plus it's super affordable!

name: SuperStay Full Coverage Powder Foundation
reviews-text: I decided to try this product out of frustration because Ulta has been out of my shade of mineral powder foundation for the last 4 months (on-line and in-store). Poor and disappointing substitute...

name: Skin Illusion Natural Hydrating Foundation
reviews-text: This is a foundation that's actually beneficial to skin. It's improved the way my skin looks and it doesn't separate, settle, melt, cake, nothing! It's buildable and natural with a thin consistency. It gives a nice soft glow. Not matte, not what I'd call dewy either. I have super sensitive skin. Everything breaks me out. This doesn't. I also am pale but Mediterranean so my skin tone is a yellow/olive and that's hard to find as most are darker when in that shade. I love this foundation and I don't mind the price either. I wear it 5 days a week and a bottle lasts me probably 4 months. A little goes a very long way. If you're looking for full coverage this may not be ideal for you, but it does a great job at making your natural skin look just a little better.

name: Beyond Perfecting Powder Foundation + Concealer
reviews-text: Love this foundation! I can build it heavier if I want but usually brushing on one layer is fine. It covers the redness and evens out my skin tone. I use a long handled kabuki brush to "burnish" the powder into my skin. Fantastic!

name: PRO Soft Focus Longwear Foundation
top-positive-review: Makes skin looks so natural and healthy!

name: Liquid Minerals A Foundation
reviews-text: Gorgeous product! I have used Liquid Minerals for 15 years. Magically, it feels light on my skin, yet it provides coverage that evens out my skin tone. At 48, it smooths fine lines and wrinkles and minimizes pores. It might sound dramatic, but this foundation will make your skin luminous. I love, love, love Liquid Minerals!!! I add Amazing Base if I want more coverage or a matte finish.

name: CC+ Cream with SPF 50+
top-positive-review: Give it a chance!

name: The Healthy Foundation SPF 20
reviews-text: I like  This foundation I like the ease of application And the natural dewy finish. it has a light to medium coverage and on me with a good primer and setting with power it has a staying power of 6-7 hours.  I wish I had a bigger range of shades.

product-links: Amazonian Clay Full Coverage Airbrush Foundation

I tried with and without primer. Setting powder made it even worse. I had to rewash my face- it was that bad. If I could return it I would. Super disappointed

Probably won?t be using there foundations or face products ever again because of this bad experience?

I don't have much to cover besides some redness and one or two breakouts and it didn't even come close to covering that. For as much money as this product is, it should do what it claims. I'm re...

reviews-text: It does not go on smoothly or evenly

name: Skin Love Weightless Blur Foundation
reviews-text: In general I'm a huge fan of Becca. Was so excited to get this but just doesn't work for me at all. Provides decent coverage but stuck to every dry patch on my face and made me look dry and cakey. It's also very yellow.

product-links: Dream Urban Cover Flawless Coverage Foundation SPF 50
name: Dream Urban Cover Flawless Coverage Foundation SPF 50
reviews-text: Very good Foundation for price point. Great coverage,  feels light.
review-keyword: Very good coverage feels very light. Kept good color all day

name: Beyond Matte Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: I've just started my second bottle of this foundation, so obviously like it.  I wear M4, and had the color matched at the retail store in Great Barrington, which was helpful as I would have chosen a lighter color.  At first I thought the product might be too thick, but applying it with a brush makes all the difference.  I splurged and bought the Iredale countour brush and really like it.  I find the foundation can double as a concealer.  However I still like a light moisturizer underneath.  I like a medium coverage and find it lasts all day.

product-links: Full Spectrum Matte Ambition All Day Foundation
name: Full Spectrum Matte Ambition All Day Foundation
reviews-text:
Here we go again.  As we approach a new decade in the millennium I am so disgusted in how cosmetics businesses continue to act like that all black women have the same skintone and type.  You keep suggesting the same color match for almost every person who ask.  
I am sure since you have created 50 million shades of "porcelain bisque or white ivory" ther has to be at least one accomplished chemist in your midst who can create a spectrum of colors that compliment darker skin. Period.

name: Bio Base Pressed Foundation
reviews-text:
As a long time makeup artist, I was thrilled to find a BAKED POWDER that was from a clean makeup brand.   In my experience, baked powders give a beautiful dimensional  glow to the skin, while still setting any product that is underneath. 

I have applied this powder with various application tools and i love them all. My skin still feels like it can breath, my face complexion is elevated to the next level, while still living in my clean standards of beauty product. A++++ W3ll People

name: Tinted Cover Foundation
reviews-text: Very disappointed.  First, you get very little product for the price, not even three-quarters of an ounce.  The pump on my tube stopped working after the second or third use -- I thought I could just screw off the cap and use it that way, but nope -- the cap doesn't come off.  I had to cut open the tube to get to the product, at which point it was such a mess that it wasn't worth bothering with.

product-links: Conceal + Perfect Smooth Finish Cream-To-Powder Foundation
name: Conceal + Perfect Smooth Finish Cream-To-Powder Foundation

name: Beyond Perfecting Foundation + Concealer
reviews-text:
Hey guys! I've been using this product for a couple of years now. Just now leaving a review! 😅 
This product is amazing. If I could give it 1000 stars, I most certainly would! It's so full coverage. I love the concealer+foundation mix. It's perfect. Doesn't leave any streaking, lasts FOREVER because it doesn't take much to get that coverage, definitely lives up to all of its claims, there are so many different color options, it's buildable, there are so many great things about this product! I usually use a cheaper foundation if I'm just running a couple quick errands and use this for work, going out, etc. When I use my cheaper foundation.. I use this one for my concealer! Which is awesome! There's just toooo many good things to say about it. It's definitely worth the price. Ladies, if you haven't given this a try.. DO SO NOW! 😍

reviews-text: My sister gave this to me cause it was too light for her skin tone and she felt it accentuated lines. I felt it was perfect! It gave me a beautiful velvety-matte finish, great coverage, and yet was lightweight. I got repeated compliments and have used my bottle up.
review-keyword: Very under rated. How had I never heard of this?

product-links: Conceal + Perfect Smooth Finish Cream-To-Powder Foundation
name: Conceal + Perfect Smooth Finish Cream-To-Powder Foundation
reviews-text: I have only tried to use this for about a week as my new foundation (not as a bronzer) but I'm not super impressed. It did seem long lasting but clung to my dry patches. I've found that if I only apply to my normal skin areas that works pretty well. Great selection of shades. I usually wear mineral makeup because I have oily t zone and dry cheeks. I still wear a mineral powder foundation on top of this and then use a setting spray. That seems to add a bit of moisture back into my face and keeps the product from clinging otherwise it would be too cakey looking. I will try and use up this product but will not repurchase.

name: PRO Soft Focus Longwear Foundation
reviews-text: This foundation is amazing, I'm so happy that I bought it. I have sensitive skin, so I wanted a foundation with ingredients that wouldn't break me out, felt light on my face but gave me good coverage, and didn't budge (I hate touching up throughout the day). Basically, I wanted a magic wand. But this LORAC PRO Soft Focus foundation checks all the boxes! It goes on so smoothly, lasts all day, covers up the things I want to hide (acne scars, redness) and doesn't break out my face. I'm in love!
review-keyword: Where have you been all my life?

product-links: 4-In-1 Love Your Selfie Longwear Foundation & Concealer

reviews-text: This is the best foundation I have ver owned. I have dry dehydrated skin that is prone to hormonal breakouts and really dark circles. With the full coverage foundation my skin looks completely airbrushed and I do not need any concealer. This mixes well with other brands products. This foundation will last me over 12 hours and still look fabulous. For me it has a satin finish and even though I have dry skin I am able to powder my entire face after using it. It works for young and old and covers my acne/ hyperpigmentation/ and dark circles easily I have  used over 5 bottles of this and it will always be my go to foundation. Everyone with every skin type that I have recommended this to loves it.

name: Skin Perfecting Comfort Matte Foundation
reviews-text: I love this foundation. I have been searching for a long time for an affordable brand that does everything for me a high end brand would do. Goes on easy, blends very nice and last all day! Does not feel heavy at all, so it truly is a comfort matte. I would prefer it to be a tad bit more matte because I have oily skin and I still get a small shine by the end of the day. However, I will continue to buy.

I prime my makeup, set it and use setting spray and it always always always makes my chin look greasy, sinks into my pores and then ends up coming off halfway through the day. It always sticks to my dry spots from my acne but that happens with most foundations. Otherwise it's gorgeous on the rest of my face! I just wouldn't recommend it if you have oily skin.

name: Skin Perfecting Comfort Matte Foundation
reviews-text:
I hate this foundation. I used it with several types of primers and it broke up on top of most of them. I can prep my skin all I want and have the plumpest, glowiest skin moment of all time, yet this stuff sucks up any moisture and good oil out of my skin as soon as I dab it on my face.

It's the kind of makeup that I put on and I just want to cry out of frustration and just wash my face and start over as soon as I get a close up view. Also it's not buildable, just cake-able on me. There's no pump and this stuff isn't necessarily thick but it is slower moving so you have to work a little for it to come out.

reviews-text: I tried it out and let me say this thing covers up everything. I have acne problems always have since 14 yo but right now I see a huge difference in my face. It's so hard to explain but I see a difference in how my skin glows. I use the setting powder 5 min after I've applied the cover creme but of course if I'm in a hurry I'll just apply it right after and it still looks nice. The only bad thing for me is that When I sweat I only kind of sweat in my face so the foundation becomes very shiny and that's not cute so I always carry from oil absorbing papers.

review-keyword: If you have oily skin try it more than once

product-links: Studio Skin Full Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
name: Studio Skin Full Coverage 24 Hour Foundation
reviews-text: I researched this foundation until I was blue in the face! From youtubers to reading almost every review. I was extremely hopeful and I just had to try it for myself. I used to be a huge estee lauder double hour wear fan. But either my skin has changed or the product itself but it doesn't look right on my skin anymore. I read on some this still had full coverage without the cake so I wanted to give it a go. One thing that was VERY difficult was choosing the right shade. This is not the kind of foundation that can be tried just by sight of swatch. It does oxidize on the skin but the color was still too light for me. Aside from the shade, it seeped into my pores and fine lines. I have combination skin but lately it has been more on the dry side. I decided to use it with a moisturizer and smash box photo finish primer. It was a little better but the problem was still present. I'm 30 years old and I don't have bad skin but I also don't have injections in my face lol I feel if I had smoother or younger skin this would sit nicely. That is not the case for me! It's still highlights my pores around my nose and fine lines around my eyes or forehead. Unfortunately, I have to pay for shipping to return the item which I think is unfair due to the fact that stores are closed and I'm unable to return to the store and find something else for my skin and my shade. It definitely inhibits me from ordering a foundation online from them until this quarantine is done and I can test them in stores. I wish they would at least pay for shipping return labels so we can still try products and find satisfaction in a purchase.
review-keyword: Sinks into fine lines and pores

name: Say What?! Foundation
reviews-text:
This foundation is amazing.

Consistency is more liquidy than what I'm used to, but this spread so easily and effortlessly with a brush. It worked well with my everyday primer, and did not leave my face feeling dry even after setting with a light powder and setting spray.

I normally like full coverage, but after one round of application I loved how natural it looked and didn't feel like I needed to add more layers. It looked just like my skin but simply healthier and evened out. ( this took 2 full pumps to achieve on me, and I'm a guy with a big face ) 

This does have a subtle scent, but it is not overwhelming and it quickly went away after applying. I actually really liked it, much subtler than others I currently own.

My problem areas ( t-zone ) did get a bit oily throughout the day, but this is entirely me and is completely normal.  And even then, the foundation stayed in place until the end of the night when I washed and cleansed my face.

Really love this, definitely a new favorite.

name: Youthful Glow Foundation Serum Drops
reviews-text:
If you are looking for a light and luminous foundation, then this foundation is definitely worth a try. I applied it with paddle brushes from several brands (e.g. Tarte Double Duty Beauty Paddle to Perfection Foundation Brush, Real Techniques Blend + Blur Foundation Brush), and I always got a beautiful, blurred finish. However, I like medium-to-full coverage, which this foundation doesn't provide on its own, so I mixed it with the Fenty Beauty Pro Filt'r Matte Foundation to provide more coverage and to help my foundation last for an entire work day.

The negative comes from the packaging, which is absolutely terrible. It is hard to get product out with the dropper. Then, when I close the top, foundation leaks out of the sides, and the clean up process is messy and wastes more product. I also have to remember to shake the bottle well and to always apply it with a paddle brush, which can be a hassle because I only have a few of those kind of brushes.

I received this as a Diamond gift, which I appreciate because I most likely would not have tried this foundation on my own. However, I do not see myself purchasing this foundation unless the packaging is redesigned.

reviews-text: This foundation went on a bit patchy but nothing a little powder and concealer couldn't even out. I thought it looked great throughout the day but I was standing several feet back from the mirror, my skin looked hydrated, glowing and even. I was horrified to see just how much it had settled in fine lines and pores when I looked up close at the end of the day. It also faded in areas around my nose and on my chin even though I never touch my face. My face also felt oily at the end of the day even though I have super dry skin. I would try it again if they release a .5 shade which is a better match for me and would probably blend better on my skin. I've been using this on the weekends or for quick errands where I just want a little color correction and won't be wearing make for more than a few hours.

name: Power Play Foundation
reviews-text:
I actually wanted to love this product, and tried really hard to. I loved its dry down, it was easy to blend on top of, I did not have to set the product. Its finish was great, exactly what I was looking for. It did not have a Full Coverage as it described but it had a good medium coverage. I tried several different methods to apply this foundation but never found the right one. Brush, sponge, fingers, wet sponge, different primers. This isn't the easiest to blend out. The best "application" I got was with a damp sponge, but the foundation broke down twice as quick. Using a dense brush was the best coverage I got, but I felt like I had to use twice as much foundation to cover my face. I really liked this product, but I didn't think for the price I was getting the best bang for my buck, Maybe if it goes on sale. 
Good medium coverage, powdery soft finish. Not super oil absorbing, I did have to powder about 6 hours in. Great for the days where I didn't have a lot of breakouts.

reviews-text: I wanted to like this for how comfortable it feels, but it has too many issues on my skin. It emphasized every bit of texture I've got and clings to dry patches. Most product was worn away or gunked up around movement areas by the 10 hour mark. You can see close-ups in my review on youtube (geek out of water). If you're not dealing with texture issues or dry skin, this might work for you, but on dry, mature skin, it was a no-go for me. I had the same problems with the concealer, unfortunately. In terms of color, the lightest shade Porcelain is not very fair. It is almost an exact match to the Estee Lauder Double Wear Stay in Place in 1C1 Cool Bone. I'm usually mid to dark in the "fair" range of most foundations. This shade was a very good match for me, but if you're more pale, it will likely be too dark.

Whether it's taking the time to blot my nose or just feeling self conscious throughout the day, I have struggled with oily skin and end of day cake face. From trying high and low end foundations, this has absolutely beat them ALL. I used the NYX angel veil primer underneath, Kat von d loose setting powder, and the new matte morphe setting spray and this is THE BEST COMBINATION. Not one ounce of oils or shine seeps through my skin. Even at the end of my day I don't even feel the need to touch anything up or redo my makeup for a night out. If you have oily skin you need this in your life !!!

product-links: Clear Complexion Make Myself Clear Makeup
name: Clear Complexion Make Myself Clear Makeup
reviews-text:
I've been using this brand in Buff for over 6 years. My total go to and when I am breaking out I look forward to using this to dry up my acne. Not full coverage but that's what I like still show my features and freckles so it's. Or a shock when people see me barefaced. Feels good to wash off at the end of the day with no breakouts and inflammation, actually helped me stay clear. Anyways, a couple months ago I ran out and was trying to find it but was having a hard time. Didn't realize they changed their image. It didn't say new look or formula on their new label so I expected it would apply and work the same way. 

I work part time so those are days I apply makeup. I noticed by the end of the day my makeup has been dried out and cracking which shouldn't happen because my off days I stay moisturized. And I'll have a clogged pore and irritated spots every time by the end of the day! Never been so happy to wash it off. 

I looked up why and apparently they upped the salicylic acid from 0.5 - 2.0%. This messes up with my skincare regimen and causing irritation. It's frustrating because the company didn't address the change in the product. I didn't bother to search up what else may have changed, so I just tossed it in the trash. Back to the drawing board on finding the perfect foundation !! 

Also on here Ulta site, it is still listed as 0.5% SA showing the NEW label image which is false.

name: Stay Naked Weightless Liquid Foundation
reviews-text: I'll start off by saying I have had problematic skin and have suffered from acne since I was around 11 years old.  I'm in my mid 30's now and have managed to keep my acne under control (a few blemishes at a time) for about the last 10 years but my skin is super sensitive, disgustingly oily and prone to congestion.  There are literally only 3 or 4 foundations I can use that don't aggravate my skin.  Since Urban Decay stupidly decided to discontinue their tried-and-true, cult classic Naked Skin foundation, I felt safe making this my new go-to.  The coverage is medium at best, taking 3 full pumps to obtain that coverage which is quite a bit and unfortunately did not keep my oil under control throughout the day.  I started using this back in December and it took about two weeks of using that I started breaking out but I honestly didn't think it was from the foundation--generally if something is comedogenic for me, I break out within just a day or so.  I really felt all these breakouts were hormonal given my age.  Fast forward to the end of March and I've had the worse acne ever.  My face is full of large, red, painful cystic acne on top of skin texture that looks like a popcorn wall.  I finished the bottle and with high hopes switched back to Becca Ever-Matte foundation.  Within about a week of switching foundations my skin has gotten so much better!  Acne cysts less painful and inflamed and skin less textured. I have since researched some of the ingredients in this foundation and was surprised to read about one such ingredient "Acrylonitrile/​Methyl Methacrylate/​Vinylidene Chloride Copolymer" which is a plastic and is used in acrylic nails.  It can be very comedogenic because it is a plastic it can occlude the skin.  It's also listed as an endocrine disruptor.  According to the CDC website,  acrylontrile is extremely carcinogenic.  Why on earth would Urban Decay choose to put such an ingredient in something we are applying to our faces? Would never repurchase.

name: Outlast Stay Fabulous 3-In-1 Foundation
reviews-text:
I have tried nearly every drugstore foundation and many high-end foundations in search of the best one for my skin. I have oily, acne-prone skin with rosacea and scarring. I need foundations to last through a long work day and to provide full coverage. I have very pale skin with a yellow-neutral undertone, which can be hard to match. 

This foundation is a great product in a few ways: it is long lasting and provides full (medium buildable) coverage. I would agree that it is 3 in 1: I don't have to use a primer with this, and I don't need concealer either.  It is great for vacations because I don't need as many products, and it has SPF! The locking pump is also great. It goes on matte and becomes a natural looking finish after about an hour on my skin. After a full, long day, it can begin looking oily. Another bonus for my sensitive skin is that I have never broken out from wearing this foundation. 

I personally have fine lines and this creases pretty quickly for me. It is not transfer proof (but what is). My biggest issue is the color - if there was a lighter, less pink based pale color, then this would be maybe five stars. The lightest color, 805, goes on nearly a match for me but after oxidizing it is clearly not a match. I have to blend this with another foundation to get a closer color.

reviews-text: I don't wear a lot of makeup, but have noticed some aging and under eye circles that I wanted to find something to "fix" without looking painted or covering my freckles. I visited a MAC store near my hotel in Vegas and discussed my concerns with an artist (Gregory) who recommended this foundation stick to spot conceal and I love it! It's a perfect match for my fair skin, blends so easily so I don't have to cover my whole face with it (just my red areas and my dark circles) and it even blurs my pores while allowing my freckles to shine through. My husband prefers no makeup, and this makes us both happy by covering my problem spots while not looking "all made up." I agree with other reviewers that it can look a little dry, but Gregory gave me a good tip about spritzing my brush with some setting spray for when I blend and that works great for me! Also have no problem with it lasting all day (or longer). I even forgot to remove my makeup after our late flight home, and my makeup still looked perfect the next morning! My only concern is that the 13 is as light as it goes. My daughter is SO much lighter than me, so I'm hoping that by the time she's old enough to start using makeup there will be more options for her very porcelain skin.

reviews-text:
Great product, love it. My biggest problem with brands is that they don't have a big enough range to help with differences in clientele shade/tone. I would even be thrilled if they didn't carry my shade in stores but did online, but sadly this is not the case. As someone who is of nordic descent majority of brands (especially in the usa and international) don't carry shades that are diverse and inclusive enough. Frankly I don't want to look like a orange when I walk outside and go to work and or out shopping.

Please broaden your range, the costumer base will thank you and come to buy your products. Fenty Beauty and Nyx are showing what drugstore brands and luxury brands can do for range of products and are listening to consumers, step up to the plate and compete. 

I was hoping that the color of the product could be lightened with Manic Panic Virgin Dream-tone Gothic Foundation Vampire White or L.A. Girl Pro Matte Mixing Pigment Foundation but sadly didn't do well, I bought it because in the store it was beautiful in its coverage and performance.

For those who have darker complexions than mine it could work well but for deeper skin tones (darker than cool deep) it will not do well.

I have combo skin so very oily in the summer and spring and dry in the winter and fall but it stays on all day and looks flawless for 8+ hours!!! Doesn't dry out my skin or make me look greasy! This will still be a go-to for me on days where my skin is behaving.

I bought once shade darker since I was mixing it with white sunscreen and it's a perfect match. I use just one drop with a 2-pea-sized dollop of sunscreen, so it's gonna last a while, too!

name: Power Play Foundation
reviews-text: This foundation seemed to tick all my boxes for what I need in a foundation: Long-lasting, medium to full-coverage, soft matte finish, controls oil throughout the day. The actual performance did not fulfill these promises. It looks nice when I first put it on (a bit powdery at that) but it doesn't do any better at keeping my oil controlled throughout the day then any other regular foundation. Application-wise, it dries quickly and doesn't oxidize too much. It's not the worst but it's also not the best. However, for the price I'll try a foundation that's cheaper next time.

name: Hide & Chic Fluid Foundation
reviews-text: I'll start with my skincare routine, but spare a lot of the boring details. After cleansing, I apply 8 products – serums, oils, moisturizers,sunblock – to my face. Finding a foundation that will go on and stay on is difficult, not impossible, but difficult. On a recommendation from a friend who also considers skincare most important, I purchased this. My first purchase was through Stila. I found what I thought should have been my usual color, but when I received it, it was too light and a just a tad too pink. Still, I wanted to test it. It's a thin, watery foundation, which I'm familiar with because of my Chanel. I quickly figured out that it goes on best when doing one area at a time, smoothing it in with my fingers, running my Clarisonic Foundation Brush over my face, then quickly bouncing a BeautyBlender around my hair line. It doesn't take any longer than any other foundation application for me. My concealer goes on effortlessly. It lasts all day. My skincare doesn't disrupt it, and it leaves this beautiful, natural, skin-like finish. I decided to keep the color that was too light, and buy a shade that in most foundations would have been too dark, then mix them together. It was a good call. I grab for this foundation more than any of my others, and I have a lot of great foundations. I would have given this 5 stars if the color selection would have been made a little easier to figure out. Then again, if I would have taken the time to look up swatches, I may have gotten the right color on the first try. For reference my skin concerns and battles are fine lines, combination, oily/dry, and my skincare routine is built around moisturizing. I've learned that if I moisturize properly, my skin doesn't secrete oils that congest my pores. I have light skin with yellow undertones.
review-keyword: This foundation is amazing, after you figure out...

This foundation is working out great so far, my skin actually seems less oily throughout the day (using with Juice Beauty primer and CC cream underneath) and the foundation doesn't accentuate or settle in my fine lines.  This is a major win! Foundation that is vegan, organic, cruelty free, good for your skin and actually WORKS is a unicorn.  Blends out easily with a beauty blender and stays put on my face with setting powder on top.  My only gripe is that I do wish they had one shade lighter for pale skin. The shade range is very inclusive for drugstore, but I wish that they had a few lighter shades. I wear 120 because of my yellow undertone, but they don't have a shade light enough for my sister.

name: Flawless Fusion Ultra-Longwear Foundation
reviews-text:
my skin has done a dramatic change this winter and I'm now the happy owner of about 8 different new foundations. Since I have little time to go to store and deal with testers, take home and then go back once I pick ( those that buy abs return, know that all products are being tossed away, this beings up our cost and it's just bad manners) I rely on reviews. All I can say is this must have been given away as PR and that's why all the great reviews on YouTube.  After put this one lightly with a beauty blender, it looks ok, then a few minutes later its setting, my pores look magnified, my skin looks cakey dull and lifeless.  I thought it was the primer. the next day I did my same routine, used a different primer. Same effect. 
this went on for 5 days. I'm done. tonight both bottles go into my giving bag. 

if possible, please at least get a couple of testers and use them first.  With tax I spent over $100 on junk.

reviews-text:
I tried this product in store and was excited to try it out because it was plant based and natural! I was looking for a more organic option and thought this would be good. When I first applied it I thought it covered great and felt great other than a little cakey, but I could work with that.

After using this for a couple months, I was very disappointed in this foundation. I had to use a lot of product to get a medium to full coverage so I ran out of this bottle in 2 months with moderate everyday use. Usually bottles this size last me 3-4 months or even longer, so it felt like a lot of money for such a short usage. 

The most disappointing thing was that as I was wearing it, throughout the day I could see the pigment separate on my skin leaving my face spotted and oily! 

As soon as the foundation got even the slightest drizzle of rain or a tear on an emotional day, it just ran right off and left noticeable streaks. It also came off and transfered very easily. It felt like a lot of the makeup ended up coming off throughout the day or made me look sweaty/oily even in the dead of winter. Very disappointing. :(

I love their mission and vision to be more natural and plant based, but it was not worth the money and the product did not hold up for me.
review-keyword: The foundation separated throughout the day

IMO, the Matte Ambition formula is superior to other CoverGirl foundations, and I have been wearing it everyday. It's better than most high end foundations I've tried. I gave Matte Made a chance, but was disappointed and returned it. Matte Ambition covers my acne acars and melasma very well, stays put all day with no need for touchups (makeup on at 5am, off at 8pm), blurs my large pores, and doesn't make my combo skin break out. This foundation DOES oxidise on me however. I wear Neutral 1, but it oxidises a shade darker. If there was a Neutral 0 or 00, I'm sure it would be perfect! PLEASE expand your shade range, as you have an awesome product here!

reviews-text:
I've never been a foundation person, but as I get older, I am getting redness, little capillaries showing, and just uneven skin. 
I am 51 years old, and have been using foundation for about 2 years, so I guess I'm still learning. The stuff we had when I was a teen was terrible. It was chalky and turned orange by lunchtime. I hated it, so I just lived without it. 
Since I lived most of my youth outside (without sunscreen) my skin has some hyperpigmentation. Not cute little freckles, but large age-spots. Plus I've developed rosacea, so I needed something. 
I tried over a dozen different foundations before I received a sample of this and I was hooked! I love it. It's easy to use, never looks chalky, never changes colors. 
It also lasts a long time. I'm on my second container in 2 years, so I'm getting about a year out of each pot, and I use it daily.

reviews-text: I can't even try this foundation out on my face bcz Tarte (like many other brands) is NOTORIOUS for having their shade range run way too yellow. Let me explain how I think this happens. When companies are doing shade testing, they aren't testing the shades on people who actually HAVE a cool undertone & so anything is going to LOOK too pink on someone who has a yellow or neutral to warm undertone, the shade automatically gets labeled as being cool when it really isn't. Now because that shade wasn't tested on a skin tone that actually has a very pink undertone like mine, it's going to look extremely orange on me. The shade I chose was 5 & it is described as being medium with cool pink undertones. Now the description & the picture looks like it would definitely be a match for me. When I opened it and put it on my skin, I was SURE I was sent the wrong shade & I wasn't. This happens ALL THE TIME & not just with Tarte foundations, but with MOST companies especially higher end brands. If you don't actually have a pink undertone, these companies should not deem a shade as being cool because you're not going to get accuracy when creating shades. I can't be the only super cool undertone that complains about this. Most shades are too orange for me despite how they're labeled, described or pictured. I'm tired of having to "make things work" & in 2020, I shouldn't have to! Believe me, I get it when people complain that companies aren't inclusive as far as offering shades that are not light or dark enough because it is these same brands that aren't including shades that are pink enough. I'm attaching a pic of what Tarte deems as a cool/pink shade & what that looks like up against a skin tone that actually has a true pink undertone. You tell me if I'm crazy. Oh lets not leave out how you're supposed to shake before using but if you don't allow the bottle to sit for SEVERAL MINUTES after shaking that it will leak all over the bottle too. I gave 2 stars bcz the formula might be good

After spending $30-$45/bottle on prestige brands and not getting the results I wanted, I tried this as a "quick fix" one day and I absolutely love it. I have combination skin, along with some rosacea and this went on beautifully! It's not heavy, doesn't flake. I don't like tons of coverage but I do have a lot of redness, so I definitely need some. I use this along with some bronzer and blush and highlighter and it is perfect. I am super happy with this and I don't think I will ever try another prestige brand again. My only wish was that it could last all day, but I can at least add another coat in the evening if I really need to and it doesn't ever look caked.

name: Sheer Glow Foundation
reviews-text: One of my favorite foundations right about now. I can opt for light or medium coverage from this - depending upon how I apply it. For a light coverage, usually when at home and not needing as much on, I dot a small amount of Sheer Glow around my face & neck, and use a slightly damp beauty blender to blend in. This gives a slightly dewy finish too. When I need more coverage and a more matte finish I apply with fingertips only. In either case this does slightly oxidize within the first hour or so, so if it doesn't look spot-on at first, give it a bit of time before reaching any conclusions. For me the color match is fantastic, it looks like I'm not wearing anything, very natural and a nice luminous look, or a 'sheer glow' if you like! Longevity is also great - I can get almost a full day out of this without it turning patchy or creasing. The only downside is there's no pump on the bottle - which for something at this price range I would have expected it to have as a given, and also no SPF in here so I have to apply an SPF separately, before my primer and this. On the upside though the absence of SPF means my face is much more flash-photography friendly, something I rarely achieve with any of the SPF foundations I have. -> My 'Ulta Beauty Top 7 must-have list' (thought it might be useful to share my 7 favorite beauty products of all time, focusing mainly on my purchases at Ulta) < - < 1. name: 3C Conceal Correct Contour Palette
reviews-text: First off, I have light skin; I don't have the lightest skin, but still super pale. I love NYX's other color corrector palette, but this was not up to the same standard. The product is not as creamy as the other palette. The highlighter and contour shades are so close to my natural skin color that it barely shows up on my skin. The one color that is visible is the darkest shade, and it's TOO dark. The contour shade on the other color corrector palette is way better. That said, it works for a no makeup look when contouring the eyes in addition to using the other palette. I'm going to use it till I run out, but I'm not sure I'll buy it again.

And Im a heavy sweater so this dry concealer actually works well with!! And Ive notice over time it starts to look better and better... I would say use a good Moisturizer like moisturizer like Ponds... and prime so it wont feel as dry!!!! But I do recommend this concealer..

I use very little and it goes such a long way!

It slightly will tone it down but literally won't even last for 30 minutes... And if I try to use a powder on top that doesn't really work either. Maybe this is better for under eyes but I like to use the bare minimum of makeup. Sucks, I really want to like these products because they are vegan and cruelty free. The only product I really love that I've tried so far is their mascara is very good, CC cream (not bb) and moisturizers.

reviews-text: So, me and make up, we got a love/hate relationship. But let me tell y'all this one... hands down the best one I've tried. If you got glasses try this. This concealer though has def won that fight for me.(I set it with loose setting powder:  Dermablend) If you got bags and/or crease easily, oooofff this is it. I've creased with EVERY single concealer/setting powder I've used. always have to touch my face up. except this one! I don't even wear foundation with it. name: Outlast All-Day Soft Touch Concealer
reviews-text: I like this face powder but am not in love with it. I have normal skin that can lean more dry or combo depending on the weather. I find if I use this powder with a light hand it will help my makeup last all day and make my face look flawless. If I accidentally use too much though I find it can make my face look drying. If I do have texture or dryness on my face it will not sit well, but once my makeup warms to my skin temperature the textured areas do look much better. One thing I really like about this powder is it doesn't settle into fine lines or wrinkles like the Maybelline Loose Setting Powder does. I also enjoy that there is no scent. This powder provides some coverage. This powder does help control oil. If I were to compare it to the Maybelline Loose Setting Powder though, I think Maybelline does a slightly better job. I wouldn't mind purchasing this again but I think I would prefer to try a powder from Covergirl's line that provides some radiance. Since getting older I have realized matte products are a bit much for my skin since it only gets oily in the summer months. But since we are in summertime, this powder will be well used.

name: CG Smoothers Concealer
reviews-text:
Ok listen up y'all, because I have tried a true PLETHORA of concealers in my time, full coverage to light coverage, matte to satin to dewy, and I'm here to tell you about this A+ covergirl one.

This is VERY specific type of concealer, the closest thing I can think to compare it to is the Glossier stretch concealer, because it's very emollient and has light to medium (if you build it up) coverage. Anyone who says this concealer is cakey or full coverage is 100% applying it too heavily, you should Not draw it on in thick lines (as tempting as that can be), and I find it easiest to blend under the eyes with a fingertip, but it works just as well with a brush.

This concealer is for someone like me; very dry skin, only requires light to medium coverage under the eyes, looking for a non-drying dewy-to-satinish finish. If you're not that specific consumer you may not like it, so be aware.

TLDR; if you're looking for an affordable almost-dupe of Glossier stretch concealer and you fit into this shade range, you've come to the right place.

P.S. This shade range is a joke, Covergirl, get it together.

So if you put make up on everyday you'll be going thru these FAST. Probably buying every month. But I love how it looks on me so I'll  be repurchasing.

reviews-text: I have very dry skin due to hormones, and I mean sleep with a layer of aquaphor dry skin. This concealer is heaven!!!!!! I have a solid skin care routine but I just could not catch a break with concealer. I had always been curious about this concealer so I bit the bullet and got a travel size....SO DANG GOOD! I use a small swipe in my inner corner and use the Juno & Co sponge to blend it out. Just a little swipe covers everything, if I use any more than that it will settle and look like all the rest. I DO NOT set this at all and it lasts (creaseless) all dang day and looks so nice!! I bought the full size and am so happy I tried this out. As long as you use a small amount this is a beautiful concealer.

This gives the most beautiful dewey, but not greasy or shiny, finish. It doesn't crease or cake. It feels great on the skin, blends well with other products, and has a gorgeous finish. I have combination skin and I highly recommend!

reviews-text: I am a concealer junkie and love to try new concealers. I have very dark under eye circles, but still like my makeup to look skin like and not heavy. Sometimes I will put just a touch of a higher coverage concealer with a detail brush on the very darkest spots over this concealer. The extra step is worth it to me since this is my biggest problem area, but I don't think most people would need to do that step. It lays beautifully over pores.  It is a struggle for me to find something that looks good both in my drier under eyes and on the visible pores around my nose. This lays beautifully on both and still manages to look natural! Lasts all day without setting for me. Love it!!

name: True Match Super-Blendable Multi-Use Concealer
reviews-text: This product is a huge disappointment and disgrace to all concealers. This is surprising considering how it says, "super blendable" on the stick. Lies. The concealer also gushes out the sides of the sponge placing the product everywhere BUT the spot you're trying to conceal. The way you have to twist the bottom of the stick to make the concealer come out is also weird and confusing. The concealer itself is very cakey but does provide decent coverage. I ordered fair to match my pale complexion and now I look like I slapped pancake batter on my face. The yellow undertones defeat the purpose of me trying to HIDE my pimples. If I could rate this product a zero I would. Do not buy. Save yourself and spare your friends and family the pain of having to look at your poorly blended makeup and regret their entire existence.

reviews-text: I've been using the Circle Delete concealer #2 for a few years now and it works great! I was surprised that the darker peach color is perfect for my very fair skin and conceals the darkness under my eyes really well. I hardly ever use the lighter color though and really, really wish it was available as a single color. I've tried the other concealers and prefer this one for texture, coverage, and color. Please consider offering the product as a single color with the peach!

name: Under Eye Brightening Corrector
reviews-text: After repurchasing this product 4x now, I figured it was time to give it my stamp of approval. I have hereditary dark circles that no concealer could fix. I tried orangey and peachy correctors in the past that never brightened the way I wanted. Upon recommendation from a friend, I decided to give it a try. Ever since I've been hooked! I usually apply it with my ring finger or a small dense concealer brush. It doesn't provide much coverage, but it instantly brightens like you have no dark circles at all. I go over it with my regular concealer, set with powder, and I'm all done! This is so amazing and life changing. I will continue to repurchase. I've even got my mom using it for the past few months, and she loves it!
review-keyword: a staple in my everyday makeup routine

reviews-text: With the latest virus forcing us all inside, there's plenty of time to go through my literal tons of makeup, including about 20 concealers in my collection from drugstore (this Wet & Wild) to high end. Well, Wet & Wild photo focus concealer has taken the grand prize, I'm not kidding, and fair beige is the perfect shade for this fair-cool blonde mature lady. I hadn't even tried it until recently and am blown away, the color is perfect, it wears great, doesn't crease (I set it with a touch of It cosmetics bye bye pores or my Elf undereye powder, they're all pretty much the same to me). I used to carry some cosmetics in my "emergency" kit in my pocketbook, usually items that were of cheaper quality that I'd only use in a pinch, very rarely. I had stuck this in there having never even tried it. Well, now it's being promoted to my everyday essentials, it is THAT good. The search is over!

It was the worst smelling cosmetic I've ever used, that's coming from someone who can use the wet n wild photo focus foundation and tarte Aquacealer no problem. It literally smelled like burning rubber.

name: All + Nothing / Concealer
reviews-text: I bought 3 shades of this at the same time, and while I will say, the shades were pretty nice, and I did have a *perfect* match to my normal skin, and a perfect shade for brightening, the product itself was an absolute waste of money. There isn't a way for me to physically blend it at all, because it just slides off and removed anything and everything underneath. I tried instead using it underneath my foundation to cover up blemishes and start with a more even base and brightened under-eyes. The problem there is that as I apply my foundation, all of the concealer rubs right off. I can't find a way to actually use this product successfully, so the fact that the shades are perfect is rendered totally useless. It's difficult to apply in the first place because it's almost hard, it isn't creamy or smooth at all and it pulls on my skin as I try to apply it. I don't know what on Earth that hard little nub brush is supposed to accomplish, but it streaks the product off of the skin with no resemblance to blending. This wasn't worth the price, and I'll be sticking to my $5 E.L.F camp concealer.

reviews-text: I really wanted to love this. I loved the texture because it looked and felt very blendable. But this doesn't provide as much coverage as I'd like. It also looks a little dry on me, which is surprising given its almost serum-y like texture. It gives me about a light to medium coverage, and I can still see the discoloration from my under eyes very easily. My biggest issue is that it oxidizes so bad on me. I originally bought a medium shade but it turned into a color darker than my tan olive skin tone. After exchanging it, I had bought light-medium golden and it still turned darker and almost peachier. Despite it turning peachier, it still didn't do well at cancelling the discoloration under my eyes. I'll use it because I have it and I feel bad exchanging it again, but I will not be rebuying this concealer.

I started using this about 15 years ago, when my skin had virtually no issues. Now I have dark circles and a few fine lines under my eyes. In the past 15 years so many new concealers have come out, and I've tried so many of them, and returned so many of them. Boing is just the best, hands down.  If it's a 'run errands' kind of day, I use the regular Boing concealer. For a night out or whenever i need to look my best, it's Industrial Strength Boing. It covers EVERYTHING,  it doesn't crease. You don't have to tug at your eye to apply it. It stays where you put it.  It doesn't oxidize and change color.  It actually feels good on your eye area.  You can layer this and it won't cake up.  It's just the perfect concealer. It also pairs perfectly with Benefit's Erase Paste and Lemonade without looking cakey or overly made up.

I know Benefit is known for their line of brow products, which are all wonderful, but they really should spend some time advertising their concealers because they're amazing.

name: Camouflage + Matt Concealer
reviews-text: This concealer is amazing. I'm trying to find a concealer that is as good as the Maybelline Fit Me because I'm trying to go all cruelty free. I have very dry skin and find this concealer works great, even though it says it is matte. However, it is not full coverage...but it is very lightweight and buildable to a good medium coverage. I absolutely love this concealer and wish they would add some more shades.

name: Active Light Under-Eye Concealer
reviews-text: I have been using JI make up for about 10 years and have been a happy customer.  However, I have had issues with the past 3 tubes of under eye concealer that I ordered.  On my 3 most recent purchases, the applicator tube broke: the bottom part that spins to push the concealer up came off, and with it the spring and other elements required to push the concealer up and out.  It made it difficult and messy to get the rest out, causing me to waste more than half of my 3 most recent tubes, a costly and annoying defect.  Did the manufacturer change?  I have used this product for years and only recently had this issue. At first I thought it was a fluke, but 3 tubes in a row?!  I'm frustrated and am considering switching brands
review-keyword: Used to love this product, until recently

overall it's an ok foundation but I'm not purchasing it again.

Great for under eyes or covering acne. It's not too thick or thin, but just the right amount of coverage to cover what you want covered.

name: Studio Secrets Magic Lumi Highlighter
reviews-text: I never used concealer before as I am blessed with minimal darkness under the eyes. Bought this just to try as I had a coupon and I was so pleasantly surprised by the difference it made!!  It is not for heavy concealing concerns but just for subtle brightening and non-shimmery highlighting. I am Asian - fair skin and dark hair - and purchased the Light shade. This color works well for me. I advance the color up and use the handy applicator to draw on a few lines under my eyes. I use my clean ring finger to gently pat and blend the color in, extending it to the tops of my cheekbones and even the inner corners of my eyes. On my 47 year-old skin, it does not settle into my fine lines.  I love this and cannot go without it for even a single day!  I hope this is never discontinued!

It definitely accentuated the texture of my skin, which I don't want. I have used Lancome color corrector in the past which works well, but is very thick which is why I gave this one a shot. I will pass on this.

name: Skin Concealer
reviews-text: I bought this for myself, but I have pretty dry skin. After doing my normal skin routine, I did my brows and used this to perfect them.... however. It didn't like blend? It seemed kind of flaky and my skin was very moisturized. For me, it just didn't blend well or do me justice. So, I gave it to my mom. She's very tan, and I used this under her eyes & baked it... Wow it looked amazing on her. Her under eyes were white as snow and she looked 20 years younger. She wore it out and while doing yard work outside in 80 degree weather. Still no creasing at the end of the day. So for her, it worked 5/5. For me, 1/5 because it didn't work for my fair, dry skin. It was a waste of money for myself, but I'm glad my mom enjoys it. Instead, I ordered concealer from KKW with the baking and brightening powder. I wish I could give a higher review because I love Kylie Cosmetics products. I mainly wanted this to help make my brows nicer after doing them and it didn't do the job.

reviews-text: Why aren't more people in love with this concealer!? The Liquid Camouflage Concealer is able to provide full coverage being a greasy mess or emphasizing dry patches. It's cheap, it's effective. Try it.

This gives me a beautiful result, after setting with a translucent setting powder! 10/10 recommend using it this way.

The peach color I use under my eyes for dark circles. Because of the creamy texture some people might find it best to set with powder after.  Then top with concealer.

So if you're the color of a white wall like I am, skip the concealer in this line, it won't work for you.
The concealer by itself is a very nice, hydrating & everything I would ideally jump at - its just not in a shade my pasty self can wear.

I'm so appreciative that someone took the time to develop a product that's safe for skin & eyes, so even though I don't think it's perfect in terms of coverage, it's so important to take care of your health... and a relief that I can still look presentable doing it!

name: Travel Size Shape Tape Concealer
reviews-text:
After trying to find the correct concealer color and consistency for YEARS, I figured out LIGHT w/PINK UNDERTONES is EXACTLY my color. Please do NOT DISCONTINUE or change formula!  It is PERFECT.

I ordered three different samples and this really helped me figure out what looks best on my skintone.  I am not extremely fair, but I'm not a medium.  Now that I have the correct color, all my other makeup looks SO MUCH BETTER.  I have light skin with pink undertones and a little peach.  I thought I was neutral but neutral has too much yellow for me.   Please do not discontinue this color because I will be back again and again to reorder.  I have tried so many different concealers colors and brands trying to figure out the correct shade and consistency. Other brands that conceal well are very thick and not smooth enough.  The consistency is perfect and did not fall into my creases.   

The pink undertone is very necessary for me because I have dark circles and a small dark blue vein around one of my eyes.  I have had this since I was very young and my skin is very transparent in color around my eyes.  I was shocked at how well it covered my imperfections without looking like I actually had makeup on.  I also did not even have add a pink base concealer with it.  I frequently have problems with concealing this blue vein with other expensive brands and believe me, you name it, I've tried it.  With the correct shade and undertone of pink, I was able to mask the dark circle and vein flawlessly with minimal primer. I do always use an eye cream though.

 I use the IT cosmetics concealer brush and you have to use very little of this product for it to go a long way.   I will definitely be reordering in a larger size now that I figured out my shade.  I can use the other sample colors on other areas of my face and blend it in with my concealer without a problem.  Now that I have my concealer correct, I will probably be back to correct my foundation shade as well.
review-keyword: I plan to reorder the larger size.  LIGHT w/PINK UNDERTONES

I don't use a foundation but finish with a powder trying to avoid where I've used the concealer so as to avoid emphasizing any creases that decide to show up on my old skin. Another review said to let it sit for a bit before blending so it can be built up so I will give that a try. This is very similar to Glossier's skin tint in its sheerness and consistency if that helps. Definitely pass if you are looking for a thick or medium to full coverage concealer, but if you are just looking for some brightness try it out.

IT DOESNT CREASE, I mean AT ALL and I've tried it on multiple occasions with different foundations and powders. It doesn't settle in my little fine lines under my eyes and it looks great at the end of the day. While the shades are SLIM, I found one that works for me and ITS AMAZING. name: Light Shifter Brightening Concealer
reviews-text: If you're looking for a medium to full coverage concealer, this is not it. After playing with it, I have found it looks great alone without any makeup, with little makeup, and with a full face! If I use it for a full face, I will put a little under my eyes and then use my full coverage concealer. I also will use it to highlight under my brow and as well as my cheek bones and it gives me a very natural looking glow. I'm 30 years old so I'm starting to see more fine lines and have found that I reach for this more than my powder highlighters as this doesn't accentuate my fine lines as much! I absolutely love this product and hope they continue to make it!!

name: Fast Base Concealer
reviews-text: Okay, so I don't think I've ever found a concealer that I like enough to give it 5 stars, but this one isn't bad. First thing you should know, this is not a full coverage concealer & if that's what you're looking for, then there are plenty of them out there & this brand offers a couple of them too. So giving this a poor review bcz of that really isn't fair bcz it's not marketed to be one. But if you're looking for something that has a light to medium buildable coverage, blends out super easily (too easy??), brightens in a snap, then this might work for you. This is not for covering major dark circles or erasing discolorations or scars, etc. This is for light covering while simultaneously brightening. It will help conceal slight veins on the lids or brightening under the eyes or high points of the face but it's not meant to compete with a high coverage foundation. It might be good for spot concealing if you can find your exact shade match. I normally don't use an under eye concealer because it's just too noticeable on me but this is something that I've come to like because it brightens nicely without it looking like I have too much makeup on. I feel like if I want something to stand out on my face, I definitely don't want it to be my concealer. I'll save the focal point for eyeshadow or a bright lip. This would be fantastic too for those who gravitate towards a no makeup look.  I've also used this to prime my lids & it's nice for that but only if I'm doing a more natural eye look. Otherwise I use a heavier eye base or primer. The formula is light but not dry like many having thus consistency. It doesn't have that major dry down like the maybelline age rewind or elf camo. But it also doesn't erase and cover like those do either. This is different than those.
review-keyword: Different from what I was expecting

With the amount I use for my under-eye-area and the occasional blemish or red spot, this little pot will last FOREVER. I've had no breakouts or irritation and the BUFF color (second to lightest) is a perfect match for my skin tone. It's super easy to apply whether with a finger or a brush and I've found that it lasts all day. reviews-text: I used this to cover a couple of zits that I had over picked on my nose. The skin was inflamed and irritated, and flaking. I applied face lotion, then a green toned BB cream. I fell asleep with it on, and when I woke up, it was finally somewhat wiped off, as I could see the green BB cream that was under it. Another fantastic Clinique product! My only complaint was the amount of, and subtlety of, my colour choices. It was really hard to pick which one was the best match, and the Clinique rep was ignoring me and not offering any help.

name: Studio Finish SPF 35 Concealer
reviews-text: This has been my HG concealer for over 15 years which is saying something! It's a solid small pot of long-lasting pigment (I use NC42) and it lasts for ages. Compact enough to slip into any bag or purse, with an SPF of 35 which means if I've concealed a blemish left behind after a breakout, there's no way any UV rays are going to darken those marks! I don't use this for large areas as I find it looks slightly orange-y on me (yet I cannot find another shade that blends in so well when using on just a tiny area, weird huh?). What I do is apply with the tiniest brush possible, such as MAC's Synthetic Pointed Liner brush, directly onto any minor blemish in a dabbing motion, and within seconds it's as though it was never there! I'm one of those people who hardly ever touch my face at all (good job, considering...) but I guess for those that do you would need to use a setting powder as this will not stay on otherwise. One very slight issue I've had has been the transparent plastic lid caving in. Previously I've been able to push it until it clicks back in place, but on my most recent pot this hasn't been possible and it refuses to stay put. Not the biggest of problems but would be better if more sturdy. Otherwise I cannot fault this and will continue to use for as long as it's around. -> My 'Ulta Beauty Top 7 must-have list' (thought it might be useful to share my 7 favorite beauty products of all time, focusing mainly on my purchases at Ulta) < - < 1. Hair Loss Treatment: Divine Herbal Hair Oil < 2. Eye Cream: Clinique All about eyes < 3. Lip Gloss: Clarins Lip Comfort Oil < 4. Makeup Remover: Lancome Bi Facil < 5. name: HD Pro Concealer
reviews-text: I see why this has been loved by so many for so long, & I still feel it's underrated & vastly under the radar. There's a lot of shades along with some great correctors too! I chose the pink one bcz I have several concealers that I like the consistency & formula of but the undertone is off. For example, I have a VERY cool undertone to my skin, but I'm not overly fair or light so it's difficult for me to find foundations & concealers that are in the light to light-medium - medium range while still having a VERY pink undertone. You see when a warm-toned person puts on a foundation or concealer that's too pink, it's automatically called "cool toned", so then someone who has a cool undertone tries on this same concealer or foundation, it's still incredibly yellow or orangey looking on me. So companies are oftentimes testing their shades on people who's skin isn't pink enough to begin with & it's the very reason why the products that are labeled as being "cool toned" really aren't - they just look too cool toned up against a warm or yellow undertone. These brands NEED to test their shades on people that already have that truly cool undertone in order to be able to offer shades that will actually match s1 like me. It's so rare I find a true shade match & it's even more rare to find a concealer or foundation that's in the light-medium range & still maintain a TRUE cool/pink undertone. So I bought this pink corrector to add in to my concealers. I buy them deep enough & add in this pink corrector & it lightens the shade while cooling off the undertone so it's more  pink and thus a match for me. It's the only way Im able to obtain a match for my semi-unusual skin color. I'm tired of having to "make things work" but this isn't too bad bcz it has a really beautiful smooth, creamy, hydrating formula that isn't too hydrating/drying & nice pigmentation. They don't have my perfect shade, but by adding a pink corrector to a deeper shade, I can get a match and a great formula!
review-keyword: I see why people have liked this for so many years

name: CG Smoothers Concealer
reviews-text: I've been a long-time CG Smoothers BB cream user (been using it since back when it was just called Tinted Moisture).  If you love that product I think you'll also love this concealer because it pairs really seamlessly with it.  I have blue veins that peek through my under eye area.  I want to cover them but I don't want to slather on concealer that will that cake up, crease, and draw attention to the texture of the skin in my under eye area.  I've been on the hunt for a hydrating, non-irritating concealer that won't make my under eyes look worse than if I had not used anything.  I've tried: Urban Decay, Bare Minerals, Becca, ELF, NYX, Maybelline, W3LL People, and Pacifica.  While I had some measure of success with some of those I tried, I just wasn't completely satisfied with the results. Since Cover Girl announced they were going cruelty-free, I decided to take another look at their product line and give this product a try and I'm SO glad that I did.  I don't apply it like lipstick, instead, I run my ring finger on to the concealer stick to warm up the product and pick it up on my finger, and then I dab my finger under my eye.  After I've finished dabbing the product I then lightly blend with my Beauty Blender.  I gives me coverage without looking heavy, it just looks like my skin, and doesn't become a mess by the end of the day.  It pairs well with the CG Smoothers BB cream when I want a no-makeup look day and it pairs well with my foundation too, but if you're going for heavier coverage foundation then this might not be a heavy enough coverage concealer to pair with.

name: PHYTO-PIGMENTS Perfecting Concealer
reviews-text: I'm 37 years old and got my first pot of this spring of 2019. Now ordering my 3rd pot. I have a medium, olive skin tone. I've always struggled with combination skin, with plenty of oil in my t-zone. Finding a good concealer had been disappointment after disappointment. Either the color, the texture, consistency, staying power or something was always less than desirable. I'm an IT cosmetics girl for my foundation and setting power, as well as some various other IT products. I was in my local store one day, and a consultant that always can tell when I'm having an internal debate. I have a now 1 year old, and at that time she was only 4-5 months old. Sleep was more difficult to come by. Not to mention the days were insanely busy when I returned to work after maternity leave. I explained to her that I needed a good concealer. One that wasn't too slick, didn't have 100 colors to choose from (options are great, I just get overwhelmed when there's too many). I needed it to last all day, blend easy and bit cake or settle in my creases or in the oil my skin surely would produce every single day. The first time I used this, I was a little skeptical. It was hard and not super malleable. It didn't seem to spread like I hoped and had a gritty texture. I used too much then and found it hard to blend. So I learned and kept trying. I would say it took me about a week to find the best application for me. I lightly swirl my finger a couple of times and begin applying by patting onto my eyelids, under eye, nose (redness), and into any areas that I blemishes or discoloration. It warms in your finger, the trick for me is lightly applying. Rubbing it can pull on the skin. After gently putting it on, I use my fingers to gently pat it in. Then use a damp beauty blender to give it a perfect finish. It does away with any discoloration and makes my complexion look beautiful. The creamy texture also perfectly fills pores and other imperfections you wish to hide. My biggest piece of advice is to remember a little goes a long way. If you use too much of this, it will look cakey, it will settle into fine lines. If it's too heavy it can't work right. That's no fault of the product itself. So while your first few tries may be somewhat frustrating, I promise if you just have a little patience and experiment with your technique and coverage needs, you'll begin to love it. Of course it's not for everyone, but for me it's been exactly what I've needed for many years. I can easily wear it to blend my complexion on days I don't want to wear makeup, too. I think my husband is even a little jealous that he doesn't have this for his under eye circles! Lol.

reviews-text: Best concealer I've ever worn.  It's the perfect shade, glides on easily and stays all day! I hope to wear this forever.

name: Shape Tape Glow Wand
reviews-text: This product is extremely sheer with a light shimmer. This makes it unsuitable for dimensional concealing (hiding things that are jutting up from the skin, like papules and other lesions.  It does help diffuse redness and hide non-dimensional things like telangiectasia. It will cause refraction, so it's not for film use. I like it for my personal use, but have no use for it professionally. The little sponge is adorable, but as with all sponges, it cannot be sanitized to union standards. Just don't expect the coverage of the original shape tape with this version.

name: Clear Complexion Concealer
reviews-text: I picked this up on a whim after my old concealer stick got old and turned yellow. I was blown away when using it - I had been suing a formula that was liquidy and ran, and because of that spread out easily and lacked coverage. This is the opposite. It's thick, and you don't need a lot to cover up even the most cringe-worthy spots. Since it's thicker, I find that you CAN blend it, but you have to do so pretty quickly or it dries out. It's medicated and I do think it helps my trouble spots clear up faster. My only con is that they have a very limited shade range, and I think I'll be in a bit of trouble towards the end of the summer. 10/10 would recommend.
review-keyword: Best concealer stick I've ever used

name: Pretty Fresh Hyaluronic Creamy Concealer

I got the shade 320 Fair and it's similar to 100 Ivory in the Maybelline concealer.

This is not full coverage and if you have dark under eyes or oily skin this may not be your jam. I'm glad to have this on hand it blends great. But on bad acne days or redness this doesn't do the job

Doesn't blend well if you use the brush on the end, I just use it to apply, but it blends very well if you blot it out with your fingertips or blend out with a smaller brush.
This has amazing staying power and the best part is that it blurs and does not feel heavy or look creased or cake-y at all! I made it a permanent in my makeup bag!

name: Light Illusion Full Coverage Concealer
reviews-text: This is my perfect go-to every day concealer. I have fair skin and use the Fair shade, it isn't too light or too dark for my skin tone. It goes on smoothly and is easy to work with when applying, especially if I'm in a rush to get ready. I usually use this under my eyes and to spot conceal with no foundation. Even with just a minimal amount, I look instantly more evenly toned and alive! This is one concealer I ALWAYS have a back-up of! My only con would be that it is more medium coverage than full coverage like it claims, but that could also be because I don't put on multiple layers of the product. I wish they still sold this in my local ULTA store!

name: Clean Matte Concealer
reviews-text: I think the title speaks for itself. If you try to put too much corrector on, it's going to crease, that is the nature of any cream product.  On YouTube search "girlgetglamorous concealer" to see how to use this!

reviews-text:
My one con: This concealer, in the tube, smells like actual paint... I have this concealer in 325, 340, and 365, and it's the same with them all. I even bought each at different times, so there's no way this is a batch issue. It's an ingredient, or mix of ingredients.

HOWEVER, on the face, there is no smell. It's very creamy and nice to work with. It blends out with a sponge and a brush. It will give you beautiful FULL coverage. I set it with translucent powder and the finish is a gorgeous natural matte. ...I'm not sure what ingredient is causing the product to smell. I was woefully disappointed by Two Faced full coverage foundation in Cloud after it matched me but didn't cover well at all and left my skin feeling wet. I am a NW20 and use the color vanilla 010 which is a little peach toned, I also have sand 022 and is a little an the yellow side. I own around 15 other concealers both high end and drugstore and this is the best for me so far. It's not perfect but at my age I'll take close to perfect, it covers my darkness without color correcting or turning grey.
